g-you-say-how-to-ask-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eknow-it-all%20robot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20I'd%20say%20that%20while%20they%20should%20have%20gone%20with%20something%20more%20obscure%2C%20it%20hadn't%20really%20affected%20me.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20so%20na%C3%AFve.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI've%20heard%20all%20the%20jokes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWithin%20a%20few%20years%2C%20the%20mentions%20really%20picked%20up.%20I%20worked%20at%20a%20department%20store%20in%202018%2C%20and%20at%20least%20once%20a%20day%2C%20a%20customer%20would%20make%20fun%20of%20my%20name.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-amazon-alexa-skills-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat's%20the%20weather%20today%2C%20Alexa%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWhat%20time%20is%20it%2C%20Alexa%3F%26quot%3B%20Some%20would%20even%20say%20things%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20bet%20you%20get%20those%20jokes%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20if%20they%20weren't%20part%20of%20the%20onslaught%20themselves.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20couldn't%20go%20a%20few%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20much%20less%20a%20whole%20shift%20%E2%80%94%20without%20someone%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpicked-son-baby-name-unique-no-longer-trendy-angry-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eacknowledging%20my%20name%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%2C%20the%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fknowyourmeme.com%2Fmemes%2Fthis-is-so-sad-alexa-play-despacito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20so%20sad%2C%20Alexa%20play%20'Despacito'%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3B%20meme%20came%20along.%20That%20cultural%20moment%20was%20the%20peak%20of%20my%20torment%3A%20I%20couldn't%20introduce%20myself%20to%20anyone%20without%20having%20a%20dreaded%20Amazon%20moment.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20people%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fempathy-vs-sympathy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewere%20sympathetic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20others%20continued%20to%20make%20jokes%2C%20but%20everyone%20just%20had%20to%20chime%20in%20on%20my%20misfortune.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20one%20silver%20lining%20during%20those%20early%20years%20was%20my%20college%20graduation%20cap.%20I'd%20gone%20to%20college%20in%20Texas%20and%20planned%20to%20move%20back%20to%20my%20hometown%20of%20Los%20Angeles%20after%20graduation%2C%20so%20I%20decorated%20my%20grad%20cap%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BAlexa%2C%20play%20'Going%20Back%20to%20Cali.'%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20felt%20like%20my%20one%20tiny%20win%20%E2%80%94%20if%20I%20had%20to%20be%20subjected%20to%20bad%20jokes%20for%20the%20better%20part%20of%20a%20decade%2C%20at%20least%20I%20could%20own%20the%20narrative%20for%20a%20brief%2C%20shining%20moment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20virtual%20meetings%2C%20when%20someone%20named%20it%2C%20their%20devices%20would%20go%20off%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20pandemic%20era%20didn't%20offer%20any%20relief.%20You'd%20think%20working%20from%20home%20would%20help%20the%20references%20slow%20down%2C%20but%20you'd%20be%20wrong.%20During%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-using-random-zoom-meetings-found-on-youtube-pretend-work-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EZoom%20calls%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20coworkers%2C%20if%20anyone%20said%20my%20name%2C%20someone's%20device%20would%20go%20off%20in%20the%20background.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20almost%20every%20meeting%2C%20there%20would%20be%20a%20one-minute%20distraction%20for%20us%20to%20listen%20to%20Alexa%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sorry%2C%20I'm%20having%20trouble%20understanding%20right%20now%E2%80%A6%26quot%3B%20while%20everyone%20snickered%20to%20themselves%20and%20waited%20for%20her%20to%20finish.%20Then%20came%20a%20round%20of%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%20sorry%2C%20that%20must%20be%20so%20annoying%2C%26quot%3B%20before%20we'd%20rinse%20and%20repeat%20on%20the%20next%20call.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20yes%2C%20in%20case%20you%20were%20wondering%2C%20this%20still%20happens.%20I%20had%20my%20latest%20incident%20just%20last%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20memes%20have%20slowed%20down%2C%20and%20I'm%20back%20to%20loving%20my%20name%20again.%20If%20anything%2C%20being%20able%20to%20say%20%26quot%3BAlexa%2C%20like%20the%20Amazon%20robot%26quot%3B%20makes%20it%20more%20memorable%20when%20I%20meet%20new%20people.%20It's%20actually%20helped%20cut%20back%20on%20the%20misnomers%20I%20used%20to%20get%20all%20the%20time%3A%20Alexis%2C%20Alexia%2C%20and%20Alex%20are%20(mostly)%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDo%20I%20still%20wish%20Amazon%20had%20chosen%20a%20more%20obscure%20name%20for%20their%20product%3F%20Of%20course.%20There's%20a%20reason%20Apple%20went%20with%20Siri%20(sorry%20to%20any%20Siris%20out%20there)%2C%20and%20Google's%20device%20is%20activated%20by%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%20Google.%26quot%3B%20The%20most%20ironic%20part%20is%20that%20the%20Amazon%20device%20can%20actually%20be%20named%20something%20else.%20In%20my%20own%20apartment%2C%20my%20device%20responds%20to%20%26quot%3BEcho%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20%26quot%3BAlexa%26quot%3B%20to%20keep%20the%20chaos%20to%20a%20minimum.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20ups%20and%20downs%2C%20I'm%20still%20proud%20to%20be%20named%20Alexa.%20Just%20please%20stop%20asking%20me%20about%20the%20weather%2C%20OK%3F%20The%20other%20Alexa%20has%20tha