20in%20higher%20education%20stood%20at%2019%2C21%2C713%20%E2%80%93%20a%20drop%20of%201%2C79%2C147%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20395px)%2085vw%2C%20395px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160709%2FMuslim-Gross-Enrolment-Ratio-in-Higher-Education-in-Southern-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2020-21.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160709%2FMuslim-Gross-Enrolment-Ratio-in-Higher-Education-in-Southern-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2020-21.jpeg%20770w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160709%2FMuslim-Gross-Enrolment-Ratio-in-Higher-Education-in-Southern-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2020-21-246x300.jpeg%20246w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700059%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22482%5C%22%3EThe%20national%20average%20of%20Muslim%20students%E2%80%99%20Gross%20Enrolment%20Ratio%20(GER)%20between%20the%20age%20group%2018%20and%2023%20was%208.41%25%2C%20with%20women%20performing%20better%20with%20a%20higher%20GER%20of%209.43%25%20and%20males%20(8.44%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20GER%20of%20Muslim%20students%20in%20seven%20southern%20states%20%E2%80%93%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20Telangana%20%E2%80%93%20and%20UTs%20was%20higher%20in%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telugu%20state%20of%20Telangana%20leads%20the%20pack%20with%20a%20GER%20of%20nearly%2034%25%2C%20followed%20by%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20which%20lies%20at%20around%2028%25%2C%20as%20per%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20states%2C%20next%20on%20the%20list%20is%20Kerala%20%E2%80%93%20the%20literacy%20hub%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20where%20a%20total%20of%2020%25%20of%20Muslim%20students%20make%20it%20to%20higher%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImpressively%2C%20over%2025%25%20of%20them%20are%20women%20%E2%80%93%20with%20a%20huge%2010%20percentage%20point%20gap%20over%20their%20male%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKerala%20is%20followed%20by%20neighbouring%20Karnataka%2C%20with%2015.78%25%20students%20enrolled%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20the%20other%20Telugu%20state%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20falls%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20list%20with%20a%20mere%2010%25%20of%20the%20Islamic%20students%20goes%20to%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%202011%20census%2C%20the%20state%20had%20a%20Muslim%20population%20share%20of%209.56%25%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20UTs%20in%20the%20southern%20region%2C%20over%2025%25%20of%20Muslim%20students%20in%20Puducherry%20were%20found%20enrolled%20in%20higher%20studies%20as%20compared%20to%20a%20meagre%20of%20over%204%25%20in%20Lakshadweep%20irrespective%20of%20its%20predominant%20Muslim%20population%20(over%2096%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20Hindi-heartland%20states%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindi%20heartland%20comprises%20at%20least%20nine%20states%20and%20a%20UT%20%E2%80%93%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20and%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20study%2C%20all%20of%20them%20have%20an%20average%20of%20nearly%207%25%20of%20Muslim%20students%20enrolled%20in%20higher%20studies%2C%20which%20is%2012%20percentage%20points%20lower%20than%20their%20southern%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20them%2C%20Jharkhand%20has%20the%20highest%20share%20of%20Muslim%20students%20receiving%20higher%20education%20(nearly%2015%25)%20followed%20by%20Uttarakhand%20(12.48%25).%20These%20are%20the%20only%20two%20states%20with%20figures%20amounting%20to%20double%20digits%20on%20that%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUttarakhand%20%E2%80%93%20the%20state%20that%20recently%20became%20the%20first%20state%20to%20approve%20the%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20(UCC)%20%E2%80%93%20also%20has%20the%20highest%20share%20of%20Muslim%20female%20students%20(over%2013%25)%20enrolled%20in%20college%20among%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20third%20in%20the%20overall%20pack%20is%20the%20national%20capital%20Delhi%2C%20with%207.09%25%20of%20students%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community%20enrolled%20in%20college%2C%20with%20Chhattisgarh%20(7%25)%20right%20behind%20it.%20Sitting%20at%206.57%20%25%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20closely%20follows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20on%20the%20list%20are%20Bihar%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Rajasthan%2C%20with%206.13%25%2C%205.43%25%2C%20and%205.08%25%20%E2%80%93%20respectively%20%E2%80%93%20of%20students%20taking%20up%20higher%20studies%2C%20at%20least%20till%20graduation%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaryana%2C%20with%20a%20meagre%204.49%25%2C%20sits%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20Hindi%20heartland%20states%20where%20Muslim%20students%20made%20it%20to%20higher%20education%20institutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESharp%20difference%20in%20socio-economic%20indicators%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKM%20Ziyauddin%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Sociology%20of%20the%20Maulana%20Azad%20National%20Urdu%20University%20(MANUU)%2C%20noted%20that%20there%20was%20a%20sharp%20difference%20in%20socio-economic%20indicators%20among%20students%20from%20the%20southern%20states%20and%20the%20ones%20belonging%20to%20the%20Hindi%20heartland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20361px)%2085vw%2C%20361px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160817%2FTransition-Rate-of-Muslim-Students-Enrolment-in-School-Education-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2021-22.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22361%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160817%2FTransition-Rate-of-Muslim-Students-Enrolment-in-School-Education-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2021-22.jpeg%20937w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160817%2FTransition-Rate-of-Muslim-Students-Enrolment-in-School-Education-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2021-22-234x300.jpeg%20234w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160817%2FTransition-Rate-of-Muslim-Students-Enrolment-in-School-Education-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-2021-22-800x1024.jpeg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700061%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CBe%20it%20in%20terms%20of%20per-capita%20income%20or%20the%20development%20of%20southern%20states%2C%20the%20southern%20states%20are%20ahead.%20Affirmative%20policies%20by%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20like%20reservation%20%E2%80%93%20started%20long%20back%20in%20Karnataka%2C%E2%80%9D%20noted%20Ziyauddin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20policies%20%E2%80%9Cwere%20introduced%20to%20increase%20student%20enrolment%20of%20the%20marginalised%20and%20backward%20communities%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20explaind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Telangana%2C%20several%20schemes%20%E2%80%93%20like%20KG2PG%20and%20Minority%20Residential%20Welfare%20Schools%20%E2%80%93%20are%20running%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZiyauddin%20added%20that%20the%20aforementioned%20steps%20helped%20increase%20the%20availability%20of%20schools%20and%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20for%20minorities%20but%20to%20almost%20all%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20teaching%20quality%20and%20regular%20monitoring%20are%20also%20comparatively%20better%2C%20as%20we%20found%20in%20several%20studies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ziyauddin%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20professor%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20support%20system%20was%20regarded%20relatively%20better%20among%20its%20southern%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhether%20it%E2%80%99s%20entrepreneurship%2C%20independent%20employment%2C%20or%20skill-based%20works%2C%20the%20opportunities%20are%20more%20there%20in%20general%20as%20a%20result%20of%20which%20consciousness%20among%20Muslim%20communities%20is%20also%20more.%20Teaching%20children%20is%20kind%20of%20an%20aspiration%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20greater%20female%20enrolment%20to%20higher%20education%20among%20Muslims%2C%20Ziyauddin%20remarked%20that%20men%20usually%20carry%20the%20burden%20of%20running%20the%20family%20after%20secondary%20education%2C%20due%20to%20which%20they%20have%20to%20discontinue%20their%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFamilies%20believe%20it%20is%20good%20for%20women%20to%20study%20as%20men%20have%20the%20burden%20of%20running%20the%20family%20while%20women%20usually%20do%20not.%20However%2C%20how%20many%20of%20them%20are%20employed%20is%20another%20question%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImtiaz%20Ahmad%2C%20a%20sociology%20professor%20at%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Jamia%20Milia%20Islamia%20University%2C%20said%20the%20southern%20states%20were%20more%20tolerant%20and%20inclusive%20towards%20minority%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20community%20feels%20more%20safety%20there%20as%20the%20societies%20are%20inclusive.%20The%20internal%20composition%20of%20societies%20are%20balanced.%20If%20you%20see%2C%20most%20of%20the%20conflicts%20take%20lace%20in%20Hindi%20belt%20region.%20The%20political%20environment%20in%20Hindi%20belt%20is%20a%20crucial%20reason.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20minorties%20people%20are%20worried%20about%20safety%20of%20life%20so%20they%20think%20what%20will%20happen%20even%20after%20higher%20studies%20studying%20and%20opt%20to%20run%20family%20business%20or%20do%20odd%20jobs.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they%20opt%20out%20of%20higher%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20professor%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZiyauddin%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20financial%20exclusion%20of%20the%20community%20across%20the%20country%20as%20a%20result%20of%20overall%20low%20GER%20in%20higher%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20banks%20don%E2%80%99t%20support%20the%20Muslim%20community%20much%20as%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20give%20credit%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20majority%20of%20Muslims%20%5Bin%20India%5D%20belong%20to%20lower-income%20groups%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20much%20by%20way%20of%20assets.%20Their%20concern%20is%20more%20towards%20survival%20following%20more%20hands%20more%20earning%20rule.%20Due%20to%20this%2C%20the%20enrollment%20in%20higher%20studies%20is%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20the%20G%20Sudhir%20Commission%E2%80%99s%202016%20report%2C%20which%20dwelt%20on%20the%20socio-economic%20and%20educational%20conditions%20of%20Muslims%20in%20Telangana%2C%20he%20said%20banks%20hesitating%20to%20provide%20financial%20aid%20to%20Muslims%20aspiring%20higher%20education%20multiplied%20their%20backwardness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20people%20in%20lower-income%20groups%20should%20actually%20be%20the%20ones%20who%20needs%20to%20be%20supported%20through%20public%20schemes%2C%20that%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20the%20case.%20It%20is%20mentioned%20in%20policy%2C%20but%20does%20not%20appear%20in%20implementation.%20It%20was%20pointed%20out%20in%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20Sudhir%20Commission%20and%20the%20Sachchar%20Committee%2C%E2%80%9D%20noted%20Ziyauddin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20private%20educational%20institutions%20were%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20southern%20states%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20Kerala%2C%20and%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160908%2FMuslim-Students-Drop-Out-Rate-at-Secondary-Level-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160908%2FMuslim-Students-Drop-Out-Rate-at-Secondary-Level-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160908%2FMuslim-Students-Drop-Out-Rate-at-Secondary-Level-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-300x183.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04160908%2FMuslim-Students-Drop-Out-Rate-at-Secondary-Level-in-Southern-states-and-Hindi-heartland-states-1024x625.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700062%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22733%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20most%20Muslims%20belong%20to%20the%20lower-middle%20class%20or%20even%20below%2C%20and%20cannot%20get%20their%20children%20educated%20in%20private%20institutes.%20That%20is%20why%20they%20opt%20for%20public%20ones.%20But%20when%20they%20do%20not%20get%20admission%20there%2C%20they%20drop%20out.%20This%20is%20why%20you%20see%20an%20increase%20in%20dropouts%20after%20primary%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20professor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20witnessed%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20Muslim%20students%20dropping%20out%20after%20secondary%20education%20ahead%20of%20Karnataka%20and%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%20states%2C%20Bihar%20and%20Jharkhand%20were%20the%20only%20two%20states%20to%20record%20over%2020%20percent%20school%20dropouts.%20They%20were%20followed%20by%20Rajasthan%2C%20Haryana%2C%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZiyauddin%20noted%20that%20this%20was%20a%20signal%20for%20the%20states%20to%20intervene%20in%20such%20situations%20and%20frame%20policies%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20decided%20to%20scrap%20the%20Maulana%20Azad%20National%20Fellowship%20(MANF)%20%E2%80%93%20aimed%20at%20minority%20students%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%202022-23%20academic%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnion%20Minority%20Affairs%20Minister%20Smriti%20Irani%20informed%20Parliament%20that%20the%20scheme%20would%20be%20stopped%20as%20it%20overlapped%20with%20other%20%E2%80%93%20and%20similar%20%E2%80%93%20scholarships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20MANF%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20last%20nail%20in%20the%20coffin.%20The%20data%20seen%20before%20and%20after%20its%20launch%20saw%20a%20better%20enrolment%20ratio%20as%20students%20registered%20due%20to%20fellowship.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecommendations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20the%20barriers%20preventing%20Muslim%20students%20from%20pursuing%20higher%20education%20could%20include%20financial%20constraints%2C%20limited%20access%20to%20quality%20education%2C%20and%20societal%20and%20cultural%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20offering%20financial%20support%20to%20economically-disadvantaged%20Muslim%20students%20would%20help%20alleviate%20the%20financial%20burden%20associated%20with%20higher%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScholarships%2C%20grants%2C%20and%20educational%20loans%20tailored%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20Muslim%20students%20could%20encourage%20them%20to%20pursue%20higher%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20suggested%20that%20increasing%20the%20number%20of%20scholarships%20and%20grants%20explicitly%20targeting%20Muslim%20students%20would%20incentivise%20and%20enable%20them%20to%20access%20higher%20education.%20These%20financial%20aids%20could%20make%20a%20significant%20difference%20in%20encouraging%20enrolment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20study%2C%20ensuring%20that%20Muslim%20students%20in%20rural%20and%20underserved%20areas%20had%20access%20to%20quality%20education%20was%20vital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstablishing%20more%20schools%20and%20educational%20facilities%20in%20these%20regions%20and%20improving%20their%20infrastructure%20and%20teaching%20standards%20could%20enhance%20the%20likelihood%20of%20students%20progressing%20to%20higher%20education%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Fpolitics%2Fin-charts-southern-states-outperform-hindi-heartland-in-muslim-higher-education-enrolment-but-why%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2F%5C%22%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709551152000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F08140805%2FPhoto-4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmuslim-higher-education-enrolment-southern-states-outperform-hindi-heartland-says-study%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20'State%20of%20Muslim%20Education%20in%20India'%20study%20is%20compiled%20and%20analysed%20by%20former%20professor%20Arun%20C%20Mehta%2C%20based%20on%20data%20from%20Unified%20District%20Information%20System%20for%20Education%20Plus%2C%20and%20All%20India%20Survey%20on%20Higher%20Education.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmuslim-higher-education-enrolment-southern-states-outperform-hindi-heartland-says-study%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tata%20Motors%20plans%20to%20demerge%20business%20into%20two%20separate%20companies%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709550998000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-02%2F03%2Ffull%2F1675439205-1134.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2