22%3EPTI%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20leader%20also%20criticised%20the%20Agniveer%20recruitment%20scheme%20introduced%20in%20June%202022%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20scheme%20was%20against%20the%20youths%20of%20the%20country%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%2C%20who%20was%20also%20present%20at%20the%20event%2C%20claimed%20that%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20will%20win%20the%20maximum%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20the%20polls.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20Opposition%20was%20not%20scared%20of%20central%20agencies%20ED%2C%20CBI%20and%20I-T%2C%20which%20were%20being%20%E2%80%9Cmisused%20against%20them%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20prosperity%20of%20the%20country%20and%20to%20protect%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20must%20be%20voted%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20Gandhi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fagniveer-scheme-brought-to-benefit-business-house-rahul-gandhi%2Farticleshow%2F107753853.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehad%20accused%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20of%20having%20brought%20the%20Agniveer%20scheme%20in%20order%20to%20spend%20the%20defence%20budget%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20big%20business%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAn%20Agniveer%20will%20not%20get%20a%20salary%20or%20pension%20on%20par%20with%20a%20regular%20army%20soldier%20now%20will%20he%20get%20access%20to%20the%20canteen%2C%E2%80%9D%20alleged%20Gandhi%2C%20at%20Mohania%20in%20Kaimur%20district%20of%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Agniveer%20scheme%20was%20launched%20in%20June%202022%20to%20recruit%20%E2%80%98below%20the%20officer%E2%80%99s%20rank%E2%80%99%20cadres%20of%20the%20three%20services%20for%20a%20period%20of%20four%20years.%20It%20saw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fanti-agnipath-protests-rage-for-fourth-day-despite-mhas-capf-quota-announcement%5C%22%3Emassive%20protests%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709548603000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F26210652%2FFufcgtmX0AQCmkG.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fin-patna-congress-leader-rahul-gandhi-slams-agniveer-scheme%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gandhi%20also%20said%20that%20the%20'central%20government%20was%20neglecting%2073%25%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20which%20belongs%20to%20marginalised%20sections%20of%20the%20society'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fin-patna-congress-leader-rahul-gandhi-slams-agniveer-scheme%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22One%20woman%20saw%20the%20Great%20Recession%20coming.%20Wall%20Street's%20boys%20club%20ignored%20her.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20a%20woan%20stopping%20a%20bomb.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e2111590413ab8e1d853e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20chair%20of%20the%20Commodity%20Futures%20Trading%20Commission%2C%20Brooksley%20Born%20saw%20the%20financial%20crisis%20coming.%20But%20no%20one%20listened.%20%3Cp%3EAndrius%20Banelis%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20excerpt%20adapted%20from%20%26quot%3BWOMEN%20MONEY%20POWER%3A%20The%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Economic%20Equality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Lehman%20Brothers%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202008%2C%20jolting%20an%20already%20ailing%20global%20economy%20into%20near-freefall%2C%20the%20whole%20world%20was%20in%20shock.%20But%20one%20woman%20could%20legitimately%20have%20claimed%20she%20saw%20it%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20Brooksley%20Born%20is%20not%20only%20the%20tale%20of%20a%20remarkable%20regulator%20whose%20Cassandra-like%20warnings%20%E2%80%94%20if%20heeded%20%E2%80%94%20could've%20prevented%20the%20great%20financial%20crisis%20from%20exploding%20into%20raging%2C%20ruinous%20enormity.%20It's%20also%2C%20more%20broadly%2C%20an%20account%20of%20how%20systemic%20bias%20and%20prejudice%20created%20the%20conditions%20for%20a%20dangerous%20breed%20of%20groupthink%20to%20thrive%20with%20ultimately%20disastrous%20consequences.%20Understanding%20what%20went%20wrong%20back%20then%20can%20teach%20us%20an%20important%20lesson%20about%20managing%20risks%20in%20the%20future%3A%20Every%20voice%20in%20the%20room%20is%20worth%20hearing%2C%20even%20if%20%E2%80%94%20and%20perhaps%20especially%20if%20%E2%80%94%20the%20message%20is%20inconvenient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorn%20grew%20up%20in%20California%20in%20the%201940s%20and%201950s%20and%20graduated%20from%20Stanford%20University%20in%201961.%20She%20attended%20Stanford%20Law%20School%20as%20one%20of%20only%20seven%20women%20in%20her%20class%20and%20was%20also%20the%20first%20female%20student%20ever%20to%20be%20named%20president%20of%20the%20Stanford%20Law%20Review.%20During%20her%20first%20year%2C%20she%20recalled%20in%20an%20interview%20years%20later%2C%20one%20man%20in%20the%20class%20told%20her%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bdoing%20a%20terrible%20thing%26quot%3B%20by%20taking%20the%20place%20of%20a%20man%20who%20would%20have%20to%20go%20to%20Vietnam%20and%20might%20get%20killed.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20men%20could%20be%20drafted%20if%20they%20weren't%20able%20to%20get%20a%20deferment.%20In%201964%2C%20Born%20graduated%20first%20in%20her%20class%2C%20but%20the%20school%20refused%20to%20recommend%20her%20for%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20clerkship.%20When%20she%20managed%20to%20convince%20Associate%20Justice%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Potter%20Stewart%20to%20meet%20with%20her%2C%20he%20told%20her%20outright%20that%20he%20simply%20wasn't%20ready%20for%20a%20female%20law%20clerk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20Born%20was%20offered%20the%20opportunity%20to%20clerk%20for%20Judge%20Henry%20Edgerton%20of%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20Circuit%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20an%20associate%20position%20at%20Arnold%20%26amp%3B%20Porter%2C%20a%20law%20firm%20that%20today%20ranks%20among%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20prestigious%20in%20the%20world.%20Born%20recalls%20that%20she%20was%20drawn%20to%20the%20firm%20in%20part%20because%20it%20was%20one%20of%20only%20a%20handful%20at%20the%20time%20that%20had%20a%20female%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorn%20specialized%20in%20institutional%20and%20corporate%20law%3B%20complex%20litigation%2C%20mostly%20in%20the%20federal%20courts%3B%20and%20the%20regulation%20of%20the%20burgeoning%20futures%20market%2C%20in%20which%20contracts%20to%20buy%20or%20sell%20a%20particular%20financial%20asset%20for%20delivery%20at%20a%20predetermined%20time%20were%20exchanged.%20But%20beyond%20the%20global%20financial%20system%2C%20she%20also%20started%20to%20foster%20an%20interest%20in%20the%20inherent%20structural%20inequalities%20that%20permeated%20American%20society%20and%20business%20and%20what%20she%2C%20as%20a%20lawyer%2C%20could%20do%20to%20change%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorn%20thrived%20in%20private%20practice%2C%20but%20as%20the%20daughter%20of%20civil%20servants%2C%20she%20had%20always%20dreamed%20of%20a%20government%20appointment.%20As%20she%20gained%20prominence%20in%20legal%20circles%20and%20academia%2C%20she'd%20become%20acquainted%20with%20the%20Clintons%2C%20so%20when%20Bill%20Clinton%20won%20the%201992%20presidential%20election%2C%20rumors%20swirled%20that%20Born%20might%20be%20his%20attorney%20general%20pick.%20It%20was%20never%20a%20hope%20she%20voiced%20publicly%2C%20but%20it%20certainly%20would%20have%20been%20a%20great%20honor.%20But%20in%201993%2C%20Clinton%20appointed%20veteran%20Miami%20prosecutor%20Janet%20Reno%20for%20that%20post%2C%20and%20in%201996%20he%20awarded%20Born%20with%20what%20many%20considered%20to%20be%20a%20consolation%20prize%3A%20chairmanship%20of%20the%20Commodity%20Futures%20Trading%20Commission%2C%20a%20little-known%20government%20agency%20with%20a%20few%20hundred%20employees%20that%20had%20been%20created%20in%201974%20to%20regulate%20the%20market%20for%20financial%20derivatives.%20Born%20had%20admittedly%20hoped%20for%20something%20a%20little%20flashier%2C%20but%20she%20accepted%20with%20gratitude%20and%20grace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndisputably%2C%20she%20was%20qualified.%20She%20was%20deeply%20analytical%2C%20staunchly%20impartial%2C%20and%20blindly%20devoted%20to%20using%20her%20position%2C%20knowledge%2C%20and%20skill%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20financial%20system%20worked%20to%20protect%20American%20savers.%20Crucially%2C%20she%20believed%20in%20the%20power%20of%20regulation%2C%20and%20she%20had%20an%20unshakable%20faith%20in%20her%20ability%20to%20recognize%20when%20regulation%20was%20inadequate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBrooksley%20had%20the%20advantage%20of%20knowing%20the%20law%20and%20understanding%20the%20fragility%20of%20the%20system%20if%20it%20weren't%20regulated%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Greenberger%2C%20who%20would%20later%20serve%20as%20her%20deputy%20at%20the%20CFTC%2C%20said%20in%20a%20magazine%20interview%20in%202009.%20%26quot%3BShe%20could%20see%20that%20the%20data%20points%2C%20by%20lack%20of%20regulation%2C%20were%20heading%20the%20country%20into%20a%20serious%20set%20of%20calamities%2C%20each%20calamity%20worse%20than%20the%20one%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20long%20after%20she%20assumed%20chairmanship%20of%20the%20CFTC%2C%20Born%20started%20to%20feel%20a%20lingering%20unease%20with%20the%20rapidly%20expanding%20derivatives%20market.%20Derivatives%20allow%20investors%20to%20bet%20on%20the%20trading%20direction%20of%20underlying%20assets%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bderive%26quot%3B%20their%20value%20from%20%E2%80%94%20equities%2C%20mortgages%2C%20or%20interest%20rates%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20without%20trading%20the%20asset%20itself.%20By%20the%20mid-1990s%2C%20this%20market%20was%20growing%20at%20a%20breakneck%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20Born%20was%20worried%20about%20an%20explosion%20in%20the%20size%20of%20the%20over-the-counter%2C%20or%20OTC%2C%20derivatives%20market%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthe%20hippopotamus%20under%20the%20rug%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20she%20later%20came%20to%20call%20it.%20OTC%20trades%20were%20happening%20away%20from%20public%20exchanges%2C%20quietly%20and%20behind%20closed%20doors.%20There%20was%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20the%20nature%2C%20scope%2C%20and%20true%20scale%20of%20the%20multi-trillion-dollar%20market.%20What%20had%20allowed%20the%20OTC%20market%20to%20flourish%20in%20such%20an%20uncontrolled%20manner%20was%20the%20aggressive%20deregulation%20that%20had%20occurred%20in%20the%20preceding%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201994%2C%20Bankers%20Trust%20had%20come%20within%20a%20whisker%20of%20blowing%20up%20two%20of%20its%20most%20important%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20Procter%20%26amp%3B%20Gamble%20and%20Gibson%20Greeting%20Cards%20%E2%80%94%20after%20selling%20them%20complex%20derivatives%20products%20that%2C%20as%20it%20later%20turned%20out%2C%20were%20falsely%20valued.%20A%20few%20years%20before%20that%2C%20it%20had%20emerged%20that%20a%20trader%20at%20Japanese%20bank%20Sumitomo%20had%20spent%20a%20decade%20using%20derivatives%20to%20try%20to%20corner%20the%20copper%20market%2C%20leading%20to%20billions%20in%20losses.%20The%20memory%20of%20that%20now%20haunted%20Born%2C%20and%20she%20was%20also%20starting%20to%20hear%20rumors%20that%20companies%20were%20using%20derivatives%20to%20manipulate%20their%20quarterly%20financial%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20her%20fears%20weren't%20shared%20at%20the%20highest%20echelons%20of%20government%20and%20the%20Federal%20Reserve.%20In%20March%201998%2C%20Born%20paid%20a%20visit%20to%20Robert%20Rubin%2C%20who%20had%20served%20as%20Treasury%20secretary%20since%201995%2C%20a%20period%20during%20which%20the%20United%20States%20had%20enjoyed%20remarkable%20economic%20growth%2C%20near%20full-employment%2C%20and%20a%20buoyant%20stock%20market%2C%20coupled%20with%20only%20moderate%20inflation.%20A%20veteran%20of%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20Rubin%20had%20personally%20overseen%20the%20loosening%20of%20regulatory%20guidelines%20that%20had%20been%20in%20place%20for%20more%20than%20half%20a%20century%2C%20and%20he%20was%20confident%20that%20continued%20deregulation%20was%20the%20key%20to%20national%20economic%20prosperity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20to%20Rubin%2C%20Born%20was%20more%20of%20an%20inconvenience%20than%20anything%2C%20and%20she%20certainly%20wasn't%20in%20his%20club.%20%26quot%3BShe%20had%20no%20sense%20of%20the%20smooth%20collegiality%20that%20characterized%20the%20top%20policymakers%20of%20the%20Clinton%20administration%2C%26quot%3B%20journalist%20Michael%20Hirsh%20wrote%20in%20his%202010%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BCapital%20Offense%3A%20How%20Washington's%20Wise%20Men%20Turned%20America's%20Future%20Over%20to%20Wall%20Street.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BSo%20what%20if%20she%20was%20running%20a%20nominally%20independent%20agency%3F%20She%20had%20no%20sense%20of%20place%2C%20no%20respect%20for%20who%20they%20were.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20when%20Alan%20Greenspan%20sat%20atop%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20Born's%20opinions%20were%20just%20as%20unpopular.%20Greenspan%2C%20an%20eccentric%20and%20often%20enigmatic%2C%20mostly%20self-taught%20economist%20who%20ended%20up%20presiding%20over%20the%20Fed%20for%20more%20than%2018%20years%2C%20had%20begun%20his%20career%20as%20a%20worshiper%20of%20philosopher%20and%20novelist%20Ayn%20Rand.%20He%20was%20as%20devoted%20to%20free-market%20capitalism%20as%20Rubin%2C%20and%20Born%20was%20an%20unwelcome%20voice%20in%20his%20ear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Hirsh's%20book%2C%20Greenspan%20invited%20Born%20to%20lunch%20when%20she%20first%20took%20over%20at%20the%20CFTC%20in%201996%2C%20during%20which%20she%20voiced%20her%20concerns%20about%20the%20lax%20regulation%20in%20some%20of%20the%20most%20opaque%20but%20sprawling%20corners%20of%20the%20financial%20market.%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20Brooksley%2C%20I%20guess%20you%20and%20I%20will%20never%20agree%20about%20fraud%2C%26quot%3B%20Greenspan%20reportedly%20told%20her%2C%20to%20which%20Born%20wondered%20out%20loud%20what%2C%20exactly%2C%20there%20was%20to%20not%20agree%20upon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell%2C%20you%20probably%20will%20always%20believe%20there%20should%20be%20laws%20against%20fraud%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20there%20is%20any%20need%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Greenspan%20replied%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20Hirsh.%20Born%20was%20gobsmacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuoting%20an%20unnamed%20Fed%20official%2C%20Hirsh%20wrote%20that%20staffers%20under%20Greenspan%20privately%20thought%20of%20Born%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20lightweight%20wacko.%26quot%3B%20Born%2C%20for%20her%20part%2C%20knew%20that%20she%20wasn't%2C%20and%20would%20never%20be%2C%20one%20of%20%26quot%3Bthem.%26quot%3B%20She%20was%20a%20lawyer%2C%20not%20an%20economist%2C%20and%2C%20most%20obviously%2C%20she%20was%20a%20woman.%20But%20that%20didn't%20dent%20her%20resolve%20to%20do%20her%20job%20properly%2C%20and%20at%20that%20moment%20she%20considered%20that%20to%20mean%20pulling%20out%20all%20the%20stops%20to%20prevent%20the%20derivatives%20market%20from%20blowing%20up%20in%20a%20cataclysmic%20fashion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20whatever%20she%20said%20or%20did%2C%20Rubin%20and%20Greenspan%20didn't%20want%20to%20hear%20about%20her%20sleepless%20nights%20or%20her%20predictions%20about%20an%20impending%20crisis.%20They%20had%20grown%20up%20on%20Wall%20Street%20during%20an%20era%20when%20braggadocian%20machismo%20was%20a%20character%20trait%20that%20led%20to%20success%2C%20and%20when%20women%20never%20dreamed%20of%20expressing%20an%20opinion%20on%20something%20as%20complex%20as%20the%20financial%20markets.%20Born%20headed%20up%20an%20agency%20that%20was%20so%20obscure%2C%20it%20was%20housed%20in%20a%20rented%20space%20in%20the%20commercial%20district%20of%20downtown%20Washington.%20As%20far%20as%20they%20were%20concerned%2C%20she%20held%20no%20real%20sway%20in%20the%20hallowed%20halls%20of%20government%20and%20financial%20policymaking.%20They%20were%20not%20about%20to%20let%20her%20waste%20their%20time.%20With%20the%20Asian%20financial%20crisis%20well%20underway%2C%20and%20contagion%20a%20real%20risk%2C%20they%20had%20more%20important%20matters%20to%20deal%20with%2C%20and%20at%20least%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20it%20certainly%20looked%20like%20they%20had%20America%20on%20their%20side.%20Greenspan%20was%20regularly%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bwizard%20of%20monetary%20policy.%26quot%3B%20In%20early%201999%2C%20Time%20magazine%20would%20run%20a%20cover%20story%20lauding%20Rubin%2C%20Greenspan%2C%20and%20Lawrence%20Summers%2C%20who%20was%20deputy%20Treasury%20secretary%2C%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BCommittee%20to%20Save%20the%20World%2C%26quot%3B%20heroes%20of%20the%20free%20market%3A%20the%20%26quot%3Bthree%20marketeers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%20the%20late%20spring%20of%201998%2C%20Born%20started%20to%20act.%20Under%20her%20guidance%2C%20the%20CFTC%20started%20preparing%20what's%20known%20as%20a%20concept%20release%2C%20an%20invitation%20for%20members%20of%20the%20public%20to%20submit%20comments%20on%20the%20relevance%20and%20appropriateness%20of%20existing%20regulation%20of%20the%20OTC%20derivatives%20market%2C%20which%20by%20that%20time%20was%20estimated%20to%20have%20a%20value%20of%20about%2029%20trillion%20dollars.%20A%20concept%20release%20is%20often%20a%20precursor%20to%20a%20formal%20regulatory%20proposal%2C%20and%20news%20that%20Born%20was%20drafting%20this%20one%20shook%20some%20of%20the%20most%20influential%20institutions%20in%20Washington%20to%20the%20core.%20Lawrence%20Summers%20reportedly%20called%20her%20in%20a%20panicked%20rage%20to%20warn%20her%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20she%20kept%20pushing%3A%20If%20Wall%20Street%20got%20too%20spooked%2C%20it%20would%20go%20into%20meltdown%2C%20and%20it%20would%20all%20be%20her%20fault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20month%20Rubin%2C%20Greenspan%2C%20and%20Arthur%20Levitt%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%20came%20face-to-face%20with%20Born%20on%20the%20matter%20during%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20president's%20Working%20Group%20on%20Financial%20Markets%2C%20of%20which%20they%20were%20all%20members.%20Rubin%20cut%20to%20the%20chase.%20Born%20was%20playing%20a%20dangerous%20game%2C%20he%20suggested.%20If%20the%20concept%20release%20were%20to%20be%20published%2C%20markets%20might%20be%20sent%20into%20a%20tailspin%2C%20fueled%20by%20uncertainty%20over%20what%20might%20be%20about%20to%20happen.%20But%20aside%20from%20that%2C%20Rubin%20argued%2C%20Born%20and%20the%20CFTC%20didn't%20even%20have%20jurisdiction%20to%20make%20decisions%20about%20this%20kind%20of%20regulation%20in%20this%20particular%20market.%20That%2C%20Born%20countered%2C%20was%20ridiculous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221842%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cover%20of%20WOMEN%20MONEY%20POWER%3A%20The%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Economic%20Equality%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65df4821ce7f1785b2e47ae2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222779%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWOMEN%20MONEY%20POWER%3A%20The%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Economic%20Equality%20by%20Josie%20Cox.%3Cp%3EAbrams%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20the%20meeting%2C%20Greenspan%2C%20Rubin%2C%20and%20Levitt%20published%20a%20rare%20joint%20statement%20underscoring%20their%20%26quot%3Bgrave%20concerns%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20CFTC%20proposal.%20Summers%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20argued%20that%20Born%20even%20so%20much%20as%20drawing%20attention%20to%20the%20possibility%20that%20something%20needed%20to%20change%20in%20that%20particular%20corner%20of%20the%20market%20would%20cast%20%26quot%3Ba%20shadow%20of%20regulatory%20uncertainty%20over%20an%20otherwise%20thriving%20market.%26quot%3B%20They%20might%20have%20thought%20that%20grilling%20her%20at%20the%20Working%20Group%20on%20Financial%20Markets%20had%20served%20to%20silence%20her%2C%20but%20they%20were%20wrong.%20In%20May%2C%20Born%20circulated%20the%20concept%20release.%20Rubin%20was%20incensed%2C%20and%20Born%20recalls%20it%20triggering%20a%20%26quot%3Bfirestorm%20of%20opposition.%26quot%3B%20By%20some%20accounts%2C%20Rubin%20never%20spoke%20to%20her%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20entered%20its%20next%20battle.%20One%20morning%20and%20without%20warning%2C%20Born%20was%20summoned%20by%20staffers%20for%20Jim%20Leach%2C%20who%20chaired%20the%20House%20banking%20committee%2C%20and%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20agriculture%20committee%2C%20Richard%20Lugar%2C%20to%20appear%20on%20the%20Hill%2C%20where%20she%20was%20berated%20yet%20again%20for%20stepping%20out%20of%20line.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20of%20several%20hearings%20during%20which%20Born%20tried%20desperately%20yet%20as%20calmly%20as%20possible%20to%20explain%20why%20she%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20a%20small%20and%20relatively%20toothless%20agency%2C%20was%20terrified%20of%20what%20might%20be%20going%20on%20in%20the%20derivatives%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20the%20autumn%20of%20that%20year%2C%20as%20a%20massive%20hedge%20fund%2C%20Long-Term%20Capital%20Management%2C%20which%20had%20two%20Nobel%20laureates%20on%20its%20board%20of%20directors%2C%20almost%20collapsed%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20of%20derivative%20bets%20gone%20wrong%2C%20no%20one%20%E2%80%94%20it%20seemed%20%E2%80%94%20was%20prepared%20to%20take%20Born%20seriously.%20As%20Bethany%20McLean%20and%20Joe%20Nocera%20write%20in%20their%202011%20book%20about%20the%20financial%20crisis%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20there%20was%20a%20moment%20when%20Bob%20Rubin%20could%20have%20used%20his%20immense%20stature%20to%20do%20something%20about%20the%20derivatives%20problem%20...%20this%20was%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20clear%2C%20by%20this%20point%2C%20that%20Born%20had%20fired%20all%20the%20shots%20in%20her%20arsenal.%20One%20last%20time%20she%20pleaded%20with%20the%20House%20banking%20committee%20to%20do%20something%20about%20%26quot%3Bthe%20unknown%20risks%20that%20the%20over-the-counter%20derivatives%20market%20may%20pose%20to%20the%20US%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20credit%20default%20swaps.%20She%20referenced%20an%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20and%20pressing%20need%20to%20address%20whether%20there%20are%20unacceptable%20regulatory%20gaps.%26quot%3B%20But%20she%20was%20a%20lone%20wolf.%20Not%20long%20after%2C%20Treasury%20officials%20lobbied%20Congress%20to%20pass%20legislation%20preventing%20the%20CFTC%20from%20being%20able%20to%20regulate%20the%20OTC%20derivatives%20market.%20Congress%20responded%20by%20barring%20the%20commission%20from%20enacting%20any%20regulation%20along%20these%20lines%20for%20six%20months.%20In%20January%201999%20Born%20wrote%20to%20President%20Clinton%20informing%20him%20that%20she%20would%20not%20be%20seeking%20reappointment%20for%20a%20second%20term%20atop%20the%20CFTC%20and%20would%20be%20returning%20to%20Arnold%20%26amp%3B%20Porter%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBorn's%20Cassandra-like%20warnings%2C%20it%20seemed%2C%20were%20quickly%20forgotten.%20Even%20in%202001%2C%20as%20Enron%20%E2%80%94%20which%20had%20helped%20create%20the%20global%20market%20for%20energy-based%20derivatives%20%E2%80%94%20was%20forced%20to%20file%20the%20largest%20corporate%20bankruptcy%20in%20American%20history%2C%20regulators%20didn't%20change%20their%20tune.%20In%20fact%2C%20as%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%20assumed%20office%2C%20a%20fresh%20enthusiasm%20for%20Reaganomics%20and%20deregulation%20swept%20across%20Washington.%20Leverage%20was%20king.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorn%20retired%20from%20private%20practice%20in%202003.%20Five%20years%20later%2C%20she%20watched%20from%20a%20distance%20as%20the%20unregulated%20derivatives%20market%20that%20had%20caused%20her%20so%20many%20sleepless%20nights%20sent%20the%20value%20of%20financial%20assets%20around%20the%20world%20into%20free%20fall%2C%20bringing%20economies%20to%20their%20knees%20and%20crushing%20global%20banks.%20In%20the%20months%20and%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20it%20became%20increasingly%20hard%20to%20deny%20that%20the%20multi-trillion-dollar%20OTC%20derivatives%20market%20was%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20the%20great%20financial%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20helped%20foment%20a%20mortgage%20crisis%2C%20then%20a%20credit%20crisis%2C%20and%20finally%20a%20once-in-a-century%20systemic%20financial%20crisis%20that%2C%20but%20for%20huge%20US%20taxpayer%20interventions%2C%20would%20have%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202008%20led%20the%20world%20economy%20into%20a%20devastating%20depression%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Greenberger%20stated%20as%20he%20testified%20at%20a%20Financial%20Crisis%20Inquiry%20Commission%20hearing%20in%20June%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20Alan%20Greenspan%2C%20testifying%20before%20a%20congressional%20committee%20in%20late%202008%2C%20admitted%20that%20the%20crisis%20had%20exposed%20a%20%26quot%3Bflaw%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20economic%20philosophy%20and%20ideology%20that%20had%20guided%20him%20for%20years.%20%26quot%3BI%20made%20a%20mistake%20in%20presuming%20that%20the%20self-interests%20of%20organizations%2C%20specifically%20banks%20and%20others%2C%20were%20such%20that%20they%20were%20best%20capable%20of%20protecting%20their%20own%20shareholders%20and%20their%20equity%20in%20the%20firms%2C%26quot%3B%20Greenspan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20impossible%20not%20to%20wonder%20why%20no%20one%20with%20the%20ability%20and%20power%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20truly%20took%20Born's%20warnings%20to%20heart.%20It's%20certainly%20reasonable%20to%20conclude%20that%20sexism%20played%20a%20part.%20In%20a%202009%20%26quot%3BFrontline%26quot%3B%20episode%2C%20Arthur%20Levitt%2C%20the%20former%20chairman%20of%20the%20SEC%20and%20an%20erstwhile%20vehement%20opponent%20of%20Born%2C%20admitted%20that%20the%20crisis%20had%2C%20for%20him%2C%20catalyzed%20a%20change%20of%20heart.%20He%20felt%20different%20now%20than%20back%20when%20he%20was%20pitted%20against%20Born%20during%20those%20bitter%20battles%20in%20Washington.%20%26quot%3BI've%20come%20to%20know%20her%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20capable%2C%20dedicated%2C%20intelligent%2C%20and%20committed%20public%20servants%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20wish%20I%20knew%20her%20better%20in%20Washington%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20have%20done%20much%20better.%20I%20could%20have%20made%20a%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20Lauren%20Rivera%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Northwestern's%20Kellogg%20School%20of%20Management%2C%20published%20research%20on%20hiring%20processes%20at%20120%20major%20employers%2C%20a%20third%20of%20which%20were%20banks.%20Rivera's%20research%20concluded%20that%20hiring%20is%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20those%20critical%20gatekeeping%20moments%20whereby%20the%20judgments%20we%20make%20about%20people%20have%20enduring%20effects.%26quot%3B%20On%20the%20back%20of%20her%20findings%2C%20she%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3BLooking%20Glass%20Merit%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20the%20unconscious%20tendency%20that%20we%20as%20humans%20have%20to%20define%20merit%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20self-validating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20hard%20to%20understand%20how%20this%20phenomenon%20might%20have%20been%20at%20play%20here.%20Born%20was%20distinct.%20In%20a%20sea%20of%20economists%20and%20politicians%20in%20Washington%2C%20she%20was%20a%20lawyer.%20In%20the%20President's%20Working%20Group%20on%20Financial%20Markets%20meeting%2C%20she%20was%20the%20odd%20one%20out%2C%20because%20she%20sat%20atop%20a%20relatively%20obscure%20agency.%20She%20didn't%20grow%20up%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20like%20so%20many%20others%20in%20government%20did%2C%20and%2C%20perhaps%20most%20important%2C%20she%20was%20a%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Alan%20Greenspan%2C%20Robert%20Rubin%2C%20and%20Lawrence%20Summers%20batted%20her%20concerns%20aside%2C%20they%20were%20likely%20demonstrating%20confirmation%20bias%20%E2%80%94%20a%20human%20instinct%20or%20heuristic%20impulse%20to%20seek%20out%20and%20attribute%20value%20to%20evidence%20that%20supports%20our%20underlying%20belief%20about%20something%20and%20to%20disregard%20information%20that%20might%20discredit%20it.%20As%20the%20US%20economy%20soared%2C%20the%20powerful%20trio%20of%20men%20wasn't%20inclined%20to%20entertain%20the%20idea%20that%20they%20might%20be%20doing%20something%20wrong%20and%20that%20the%20deregulation%20they%20had%20championed%20for%20so%20many%20years%20was%20setting%20the%20market%20up%20for%20disaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20blog%20post%20published%20a%20decade%20after%20the%20crisis%2C%20in%20September%202018%2C%20Christine%20Lagarde%2C%20who%20at%20the%20time%20was%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%2C%20described%20the%20great%20financial%20crisis%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20sobering%20lesson%20in%20groupthink.%26quot%3B%20She%20wrote%20that%20in%20the%20years%20since%20the%20collapse%20of%20Lehman%20Brothers%20and%20other%20major%20financial%20institutions%2C%20policy%20has%20addressed%20the%20flaws%20in%20the%20system%20that%20ultimately%20led%20to%20the%20crisis.%20But%20there's%20one%20thing%20that's%20not%20changed%20much%2C%20she%20contended%2C%20and%20that's%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20true%20legacy%26quot%3B%20of%20that%20crisis%20cannot%20yet%20be%20adequately%20assessed%20because%20it's%20%26quot%3Bstill%20being%20written.%26quot%3B%20More%20than%2015%20years%20on%2C%20and%20with%20far%20more%20women%20in%20positions%20of%20power%20across%20business%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20elsewhere%2C%20it%20may%20be%20too%20early%20to%20tell%20whether%20the%20lessons%20from%20that%20crisis%20have%20all%20been%20internalized.%20Would%20a%20Brooksley%20Born%20today%20be%20able%20to%20avert%20a%20financial%20meltdown%3F%20One%20hopes%20so%2C%20but%20it%20may%20take%20another%20crisis%20to%20know%20for%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjosie-cox%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJosie%20Cox%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20written%20for%20Reuters%2C%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%2C%C2%A0and%20The%20Guardian.%20She%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BWOMEN%20MONEY%20POWER%3A%20The%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Economic%20Equality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpt%20adapted%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D5ef93badd442c406beec3d29c470882789ec80b00f3389dd336bbe9dd77948b9%26postID%3D65df45734aaa4153d1f7c417%26postSlug%3Dwoman-warned-great-recession-2008-brooksley-born-wall-street-sexism-2024-3%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FWomen-Money-Power-Economic-Equality%252Fdp%252F1419762982%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWOMEN%20MONEY%20POWER%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20by%20Josie%20Cox.%20Copyright%20%C2%A9%202024%20Josie%20Cox.%20Used%20by%20permission%20of%20Abrams%20Press%2C%20an%20imprint%20of%20ABRAMS%2C%20New%20York.%20All%20rights%20reserved.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-warned-great-recession-2008-brooksley-born-wall-street-sexism-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709548501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e211d56080194819fbaf88%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22