C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Maroon%20told%20Business%20Insider%20his%20family%20is%20encouraging%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20still%20works.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Dr.%20Joseph%20Maroon%2C%20ilbusca%2FGetty%2C%20Visivasnc%2FiStock%2C%20JazzIRT%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDr.%20Joseph%20Maroon%20is%20a%20neurosurgeon%2C%20professor%2C%20and%20triathlete.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20stepped%20back%20from%20performing%20surgeries%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20still%20works%20up%20to%2050%20hours%20a%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20work%20keeps%20him%20engaged%20and%20allows%20him%20to%20use%20his%20brain.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctor-joseph-maroon-triathlete-supplements-takes-longevity-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDr.%20Joseph%20Maroon%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20an%2083-year-old%20neurosurgeon%20living%20in%20Pittsburgh%2C%20about%20his%20decision%20to%20keep%20working%20at%20his%20age%20instead%20of%20retiring.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2083%2C%20I'm%20having%20more%20fun%20now%20doing%20what%20I%20do%20than%20I%20have%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20career%20began%20in%201972%20when%20I%20joined%20the%20neurosurgery%20department%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pittsburgh%20after%20I'd%20finished%20my%20residency%20training.%20I've%20worked%20in%20the%20neurosurgical%20field%20for%2051%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20my%20day%20job%20was%20diagnosing%20and%20treating%20patients%20with%20major%20problems%20of%20the%20brain%20and%20spine%2C%20primarily%20through%20surgery.%20Five%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20stop%20performing%20surgeries%20and%20focus%20instead%20on%20various%20research%20projects%2C%20and%20to%20increase%20my%20mentoring%20and%20teaching%20of%20residents%20and%20medical%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20currently%20work%20around%2040%20to%2050%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20anywhere%20between%20six%20to%2010%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20on%20research%2C%20lecturing%2C%20and%20mentoring.%20I'm%20working%20just%20as%20much%20now%20as%20I%20was%20when%20I%20was%20doing%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20going%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fplanned-retirement-until-discovered-fire-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20I%20have%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20still%20feel%20very%20relevant%20in%20my%20profession%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20operated%20on%20patients%20until%20I%20was%2077.%20I%20still%20feel%20I%20could%20operate%2C%20but%20think%20patients%20might%20question%20it%20at%20my%20age.%20Sometimes%2C%20in%20neurosurgery%2C%20the%20operations%20are%20very%20long%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20it%20was%20best%20not%20to%20push%20the%20limit%2C%20but%20I%20still%20see%20patients%20and%20consult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20desire%20to%20devote%20more%20time%20to%20research.%20I'm%20currently%20working%20on%20a%20project%20involving%20surgical%20applications%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-augmented-reality%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaugmented%20reality%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20among%20other%20things.%20As%20a%20surgeon%2C%20you%20can%20work%20with%20one%20person%20at%20a%20time.%20The%20work%20I'm%20doing%20now%20can%20potentially%20touch%20thousands%20of%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pittsburgh%2C%20a%20consultant%20neurosurgeon%20to%20the%20Pittsburgh%20Steelers%2C%20the%20medical%20director%20of%20World%20Wrestling%20Entertainment%2C%20and%20a%20chairman%20of%20the%20National%20Science%20Advisory%20Committee%20of%20the%20Chuck%20Noll%20Foundation%2C%20which%20supports%20research%20into%20ways%20of%20diagnosing%20and%20treating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftraumatic-brain-injury%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrain%20injuries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20primarily%20occurring%20in%20sports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20Joseph%20Maroon%20holding%20his%20hands%20in%20the%20air%20as%20he%20stands%20next%20to%20an%20ironman%20triathlon%20sign.%20There%20is%20a%20medal%20around%20his%20neck.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1ade06080194819fb7d5a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Maroon%20is%20the%20medical%20director%20of%20the%20WWE%20and%20a%20consultant%20neurosurgeon%20to%20the%20Pittsburgh%20Steelers.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Dr.%20Joseph%20Maroon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20welcomed%20in%20my%20department%20as%20a%20senior%20member.%20With%2050%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20I%20think%20there%20are%20still%20things%20I%20can%20contribute%2C%20such%20as%20research%20and%20giving%20suggestions%20to%20younger%20initiates%20as%20a%20mentor.%20I%20still%20feel%20very%20relevant%20in%20my%20profession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20my%20family%20is%20a%20bit%20surprised%20that%20I'm%20still%20working%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20pleased%20and%20encouraging%20of%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere's%20currently%20a%20debate%20in%20the%20political%20realm%20around%20age%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20generalize%2C%20but%20if%20the%20quality%20of%20an%20individual's%20life%20is%20such%20that%20mentally%20and%20physically%2C%20they're%20able%20to%20work%20later%2C%20I%20certainly%20encourage%20that.%20If%20you've%20had%20a%20stroke%20or%20have%20early%20dementia%2C%20these%20are%20factors%20that%20will%20enter%20into%20the%20equation%20of%20how%20long%20or%20how%20effectively%20you%20can%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20there's%20a%20debate%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-house-democrat-age-slowing-president-down-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%3C%2Fa%3E%20regarding%20cognitive%20awareness.%20I%20think%20people%20are%20aware%20of%20his%20age%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmitch-mcconnell-joe-biden-donald-trump-age-issue-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformer%20president%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20age%2070%2C%20I%20had%20to%20take%20a%20neuropsychological%20test%20as%20well%20as%20a%20physical%20examination%20to%20continue%20to%20operate.%20Air%20traffic%20controllers%2C%20pilots%2C%20and%20others%20also%20have%20to%20undergo%20similar%20testing.%20Is%20this%20a%20consideration%20for%20those%20working%20in%20politics%3F%20I'll%20leave%20that%20up%20to%20others%20to%20decide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20ages%20at%20a%20different%20rate%20depending%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiology-of-aging-why-bodies-get-old-2018-8%23errors-appear-in-dna-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenetic%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealth-effects-of-epigenetics-2013-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eepigenetic%3C%2Fa%3E%20factors%2C%20so%20there's%20no%20one%20age%20I%20believe%20is%20a%20limit.%20Some%20people%20in%20their%2090s%20are%20as%20sharp%20as%20can%20be%3B%20others%20in%20their%2060s%20have%20significant%20problems%20processing%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20when%20people%20should%20retire%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20matter%20of%20assessing%20one's%20faculties%20in%20terms%20of%20mental%20and%20physical%20abilities%20with%20objective%20scrutiny.%20Do%20you%20still%20have%20your%20senses%3F%20Is%20your%20brain%20still%20functioning%20at%20a%20level%20that%20you%20feel%20it%20should%20at%20thi