ade%20later%2C%20their%20student%20loans%20are%20preventing%20them%20from%20fully%20separating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20Rowan%20and%20her%20then-husband%20decided%20to%20consolidate%20their%20student-loan%20balances%20into%20the%20spousal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-do-separate-spousal-student-loan-debt-balance-new-guidance-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ejoint%20consolidation%20loan%20program%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20Congress%20created%20to%20allow%20married%20couples%20to%20combine%20their%20balances%20and%20make%20payments%20with%20a%20single%20interest%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20decided%20to%20divorce%20eight%20years%20later%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-spousal-loans-be-separated-student-debt-relief-forgiveness-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20not%20separate%20their%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20Congress%20shuttered%20the%20program%20in%202006%2C%20leaving%20them%20without%20any%20avenue%20to%20pay%20their%20loans%20separately.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20judge%20overseeing%20the%20divorce%20ordered%20Rowan%20to%20pay%2018%25%20of%20the%20balance%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20about%20%2498%2C000%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20and%20her%20ex-husband%20was%20ordered%20to%20pay%2082%25%20of%20it%20since%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20loans%20belonged%20to%20him%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agreement%20also%20stated%20that%20her%20ex-husband%20would%20make%20the%20payments%2C%20and%20Rowan%20would%20reimburse%20him%20for%20her%20portion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Rowan's%20ex-husband%20made%20some%20payments%2C%20they%20were%20not%20consistent%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she%20was%20notified%20that%20her%20loan%20was%20in%20default%20status%20with%20the%20risk%20of%20wage%20garnishment%20if%20she%20did%20not%20bring%20the%20account%20up%20to%20date%20on%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20combined%20balance%20now%20stands%20at%20just%20under%20%24365%2C000%2C%20per%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20BI%2C%20due%20to%20surging%20interest%20on%20the%20loans%20during%20the%20periods%20when%20no%20payments%20were%20being%20made.%20Rowan%20has%20since%20re-married%2C%20and%20to%20help%20pay%20for%20her%20kids'%20educations%2C%20her%20husband%20has%20had%20to%20take%20out%20federal%20parent%20PLUS%20student%20loans%20under%20his%20own%20name%2C%20which%20allow%20a%20parent%20to%20borrow%20up%20to%20the%20full%20cost%20of%20attendance%20for%20their%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20my%20oldest%20went%20into%20college%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20get%20a%20parent%20loan%2C%20and%20I%20couldn't%20because%20of%20my%20outstanding%20debt.%20So%20my%20current%20husband%20has%20all%20my%20kids'%20student%20loans%20in%20his%20name%2C%26quot%3B%20Rowan%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20we've%20got%20a%20second%20one%20that's%20in%20university%20now%2C%20and%20it's%20the%20same%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%20%26quot%3BAll%20the%20student%20loans%20are%20in%20my%20current%20husband's%20name.%20So%20it's%20just%20been%20extremely%20difficult%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20make%20the%20payments.%20I%20want%20to%20get%20out%20of%20default%20status.%20I%20went%20to%20college%2C%20I%20got%20my%20degree%2C%20I%20owe%20that%20money%20back%2C%20and%20I%20have%20no%20problem%20paying%20it%2C%20but%20he%20has%20to%20be%20the%20one%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22958%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shannon%20Rowan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65dfa238ce7f1785b2e4be42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22719%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShannon%20Rowan%2C%2051%2C%20cannot%20separate%20her%20%24365%2C000%20student-loan%20balance%20from%20her%20ex-husband.%3Cp%3EShannon%20Rowan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Rowan%20wants%20to%20separate%20her%20loans%20to%20gain%20financial%20freedom%20from%20her%20ex%2C%20other%20borrowers%20with%20spousal%20loans%20are%20seeking%20to%20separate%20their%20balances%20for%20a%20range%20of%20reasons.%20For%20example%2C%20one%20married%20coupled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarried-couples-blocked-from-student-loan-forgiveness-after-combining-balances-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20want%20separate%20so%20they%20can%20qualify%20for%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%2C%20and%20spousal%20loans%20are%20not%20eligible%20for%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20the%20issue%2C%20Sen.%20Mark%20Warner%20and%20Rep.%20David%20Price%20introduced%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspousal-student-loan-borrowers-can-separate-balances-debt-relief-forgiveness-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJoint%20Consolidation%20Loan%20Separation%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202021%20%E2%80%94%20signed%20into%20law%20by%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20to%20allow%20borrowers%20to%20separate%20their%20spousal%20loans.%20However%2C%20Federal%20Student%20Aid's%20website%20said%20implementation%20of%20the%20law%20likely%20won't%20happen%20%26quot%3Buntil%20late%202024%20at%20the%20earliest%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20spousal%20borrowers%20are%20still%20stuck%20in%20limbo%20without%20any%20avenue%20for%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20a%20huge%20financial%20stress%20because%20my%20husband%20also%20has%20the%20house%20in%20his%20name%2C%26quot%3B%20Rowan%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20keep%20thinking%20every%20time%20we%20try%20to%20do%20something%20that%20is%20necessary%20for%20the%20kids%20or%20our%20living%20situation%2C%20are%20we%20going%20to%20get%20turned%20down%20as%20a%20result%20of%20all%20of%20this%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'It's%20been%20a%20nightmare'%