%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Faditya-roy-kapur-ananya-panday-slay-in-chic-casuals-as-they-leave-jamnagar-after-anant-radhikas-pre-wedding-festivities%2Farticleshow%2F108203616.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108203616.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAditya%20Roy%20Kapur%20and%20Ananya%20Panday%20are%20reportedly%20dating%20each%20other.%20However%2C%20the%20duo%20has%20never%20confirmed%20or%20denied%20the%20news.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Faditya-roy-kapur-ananya-panday-slay-in-chic-casuals-as-they-leave-jamnagar-after-anant-radhikas-pre-wedding-festivities%2Farticleshow%2F108203616.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Leads%20in%20Support%20for%20Autocracy%2C%20Military%20Rule%20Among%20Surveyed%20Nations%3A%20Pew%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F24154811%2F170287540_d202b7bd8d_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIndia%20leads%20in%20support%20for%20autocracy%20and%20military%20rule%20among%20surveyed%20nations%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22file%3A%2FC%3A%2FUsers%2FTANIYA%2FDownloads%2Fgap_2024.02.28_democracy-closed-end_report.pdf%5C%22%3EPew%20survey%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20on%20February%2028.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20is%20titled%20%E2%80%98Representative%20Democracy%20Remains%20A%20Popular%20Ideal%2C%20but%20People%20Around%20the%20World%20Are%20Critical%20of%20How%20It%E2%80%99s%20Working%E2%80%99.%20It%C2%A0asked%20respondents%20in%2024%20countries%20about%20different%20forms%20of%20governance%2C%20including%20representative%20democracy%2C%20direct%20democracy%2C%20autocracy%2C%20technocracy%20and%20military%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupport%20for%20autocracy%2C%20military%20rule%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESixty-seven%20per%20cent%20of%20Indians%20surveyed%20express%20support%20for%20autocracy%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Pew%20Research.%20In%202017%2C%20it%20stood%20at%2055%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20stands%20out%20with%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20people%20endorsing%20autocracy%20among%20the%20countries%20surveyed%20by%20Pew.%20In%20comparison%2C%20Kenya%20has%2052%25%20of%20supporters%20for%20autocracy%2C%20while%20Indonesia%20has%2051%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERespondents%20were%20asked%20to%20consider%20a%20system%20in%20which%20a%20strong%20leader%20is%20free%20to%20make%20decisions%20without%20interference%20from%20a%20representative%20body%20or%20independent%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20there%20was%20a%20broad%20opposition%20to%20autocracy%20from%20most%20countries%20surveyed%20including%20the%20US%20(26%25)%2C%20Canada%20(19%25)%2C%20and%20the%20UK%20(13%25)%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20also%20added%20that%20countries%20with%20a%20higher%20GDP%20per%20capita%20tend%20to%20have%20fewer%20people%20who%20think%20rule%20by%20a%20strong%20leader%20is%20a%20good%20way%20to%20govern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMilitary%20rule%20also%20has%20a%20huge%20support%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20the%20highest%20among%20all%20nations%20%E2%80%93%20with%2072%25%20embracing%20it%2C%20the%20survey%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20over%20half%20of%20the%20countries%20surveyed%2C%20majorities%20believe%20it%20would%20be%20a%20very%20bad%20way%20to%20govern%2C%20showed%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20suggested%20that%20people%20with%20lower%20incomes%20are%20more%20accepting%20of%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20strong%20leader%20whose%20power%20goes%20unchecked.%20And%20those%20with%20less%20education%20are%20more%20inclined%20to%20view%20autocracy%20favourably%20compared%20to%20their%20more%20educated%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20however%2C%20didn%E2%80%99t%20specify%20which%20countries%20were%20included%20in%20these%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fare-we-headed-for-an-open-autocracy%5C%22%3EAre%20We%20Headed%20for%20an%20Open%20Autocracy%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupport%20for%20technocracy%20goes%20up%20in%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESince%202017%2C%20the%20number%20of%20technocracy%20supporters%20has%20gone%20up%20in%20most%20of%20the%20countries%20surveyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20technocratic%20system%2C%20individuals%20with%20specialised%20knowledge%20and%20expertise%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20science%2C%20technology%2C%20economics%2C%20or%20engineering%20are%20appointed%20or%20selected%20to%20govern%20or%20lead%2C%20based%20on%20their%20qualifications%20and%20competency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20survey%2C%20this%20shift%20could%20be%20tied%2C%20at%20least%20in%20part%2C%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20Since%202020%2C%20many%20have%20turned%20to%20scientists%20and%20medical%20professionals%20for%20their%20expertise%20on%20how%20to%20manage%20the%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20India%2C%20support%20for%20technocracy%20has%20gone%20up%20to%2082%25%20in%202023%20from%2065%25%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20elected%20officials%20care%20what%20people%20like%20them%20think%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESweden%20is%20the%20only%20country%20surveyed%20where%20a%20majority%20(56%25)%20of%20people%20believe%20that%20elected%20officials%20care%20what%20people%20like%20them%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%2055%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20believed%20that%20elected%20officials%20don%E2%80%99t%20care%20what%20people%20like%20them%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20every%20country%20surveyed%2C%20individuals%20who%20say%20their%20country%E2%80%99s%20economic%20situation%20is%20good%20are%20more%20inclined%20to%20believe%20that%20most%20elected%20officials%20care%20about%20people%20like%20them%2C%20compared%20to%20those%20who%20perceive%20the%20economic%20situation%20negatively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20if%20more%20elected%20officials%20were%20women%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%2068%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20said%20the%20policies%20in%20their%20country%20would%20improve%20if%20more%20elected%20officials%20were%20women.%20This%20figure%20stands%20as%20the%20highest%20percentage%20among%20the%20countries%20surveyed%2C%20closely%20followed%20by%20Brazil%20and%20Nigeria%2C%20both%20at%2062%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202023%2C%20India%20introduced%20a%20gender%20quota%20to%20approve%20a%20third%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lok%20Sabha%20passed%20the%20Constitution%20(One%20Hundred%20and%20Twenty-eighth%20Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20that%20seeks%20to%20provide%2033%25%20reservation%20to%20women%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies.%20Most%20opposition%20parties%20supported%20the%20Bill%20in%20principle%20but%20questioned%20the%20delimitation%20clause%20tied%20to%20the%20legislation%2C%20which%20would%20lead%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flok-sabha-passes-womens-reservation-bill-amit-shah-implementation-2029%5C%22%3Eimplementation%20not%20before%202029.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Findia-globally-a-fortnightly-highlight-of-how-the-world-is-watching-our-democracy%5C%22%3EIndia%2C%20Globally%3A%20A%20Fortnightly%20Highlight%20of%20How%20the%20World%20Is%20Watching%20Our%20Democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20most%20favourable%20leaders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20survey%20also%20found%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20emerge%20as%20the%20most%20favourable%20leaders%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20the%2024%20national%20leaders%20polled%20across%20the%20world%2C%20Modi%20has%20a%2079%25%20favourability%20rating%2C%20the%20third%20highest%20in%20the%20world%20after%20Indonesian%20president%20Joko%20%E2%80%98Jokowi%E2%80%99%20Widodo%20(89%25)%20and%20Mexican%20president%20Andr%C3%A9s%20Manuel%20L%C3%B3pez%20Obrador%20(82%25)%2C%20said%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20rating%20(62%25)%20is%20the%20second-highest%20among%20all%20opposition%20leaders%20surveyed%20globally.%20The%20most%20favourable%20opposition%20leader%20is%20Indonesia%E2%80%99s%20Agus%20Harimurti%20Yudhoyono%20(68%25)%2C%20the%20survey%20found.%20Note%20that%20the%20survey%20posed%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfavourability%E2%80%9D%20question%20exclusively%20to%20individuals%20from%20the%20opposition%20leader%E2%80%99s%20respective%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20survey%20studied%20the%20favourability%20ratings%20of%2033%20opposition%20leaders%20across%20the%2024%20countries.%20Three%20of%20them%20were%20from%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAs%20earlier%20mentioned%2C%2062%25%20of%20Indians%20surveyed%20are%20in%20favour%20of%20Gandhi%2C%20followed%20by%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20(42%25)%20and%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20(46%25)%2C%20according%20to%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20respect%20to%20political%20parties%2C%2073%25%20of%20respondents%20held%20a%20favourable%20view%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20while%2060%25%20viewed%20the%20Congress%20favourably.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20non-US%20data%2C%20the%20Pew%20Survey%20report%20relies%20on%20nationally%20representative%20surveys%20conducted%20among%2027%2C285%20adults%20from%20February%2020%20to%20May%2022%2C%202023.%20Phone%20surveys%20were%20conducted%20with%20adults%20in%20Canada%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20Greece%2C%20Italy%2C%20Japan%2C%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20Spain%2C%20Sweden%2C%20and%20the%20UK.%20Face-to-face%20surveys%20were%20conducted%20in%20Hungary%2C%20Poland%2C%20India%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20Israel%2C%20Kenya%2C%20Nigeria%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Argentina%2C%20Brazil%2C%20and%20Mexico.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709545805000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F24154811%2F170287540_d202b7bd8d_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Findia-leads-in-support-for-autocracy-military-rule-among-surveyed-nations-pew%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20stands%20out%20with%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20people%20(67%25)%20endorsing%20autocracy%20among%20the%20countries%20surveyed%20by%20Pew.%2072%25%20of%20Indians%2C%20says%20the%20survey%2C%20view%20the%20prospect%20of%20military%20rule%20favourably.%20But%20in%20over%20half%20of%20the%20countries%20surveyed%2C%20majorities%20believe%20that%20would%20be%20a%20very%20bad%20way%20to%20govern.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Findia-leads-in-support-for-autocracy-military-rule-among-surveyed-nations-pew%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BYou%20Abused%20Your%20Right%26quot%3B%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20To%20Stalin%20Junior%20On%20Sanatana%20Row%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20slammed%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Minister%20Udhayanidhi%20Stalin%20over%20his%20controversial%20statement%20advocating%20the%20%26quot%3Beradication%26quot%3B%20of%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%3C%2Fem%3E.%20A%20bench%2C%20consisting%20of%20justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%20questioned%20the%20minister's%20decision%20to%20approach%20the%20top%20court%20after%20making%20inflammatory%20remarks%2C%20stating%20that%20as%20a%20minister%2C%20he%20should%20be%20well%20aware%20of%20the%20consequences%20of%20his%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20abuse%20your%20right%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20(of%20the%20Constitution).%20You%20abuse%20your%20right%20under%20Article%2025.%20Now%20you%20are%20exercising%20your%20right%20under%20Article%2032%20(to%20file%20plea%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court)%3F%20Do%20you%20not%20know%20the%20consequences%20of%20what%20you%20said%3F%20You%20are%20not%20a%20layman.%20You%20are%20a%20minister.%20You%20should%20know%20the%20consequences%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20said%20before%20adjourning%20the%20matter%20to%20March%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepresenting%20Udhayanidhi%20Stalin%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%20appealed%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20relief%2C%20requesting%20to%20club%20all%20FIRs.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20these%20FIRs%20had%20been%20filed%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUdhayanidhi%20Stalin%2C%20son%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Chief%20Minister%20and%20DMK%20chief%20MK%20Stalin%2C%20made%20the%20controversial%20statement%20during%20a%20conference%20in%20September%202023.%20He%20said%20that%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20against%20social%20justice%20and%20equality%20and%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Beradicated.%26quot%3B%20The%20remark%20ignited%20a%20massive%20backlash%2C%20particularly%20from%20BJP%20leaders%20who%20criticised%20the%20minister's%20comparison%20of%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20diseases%20like%20dengue%20and%20malaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20escalated%20on%20social%20media%2C%20with%20the%20BJP%20accusing%20the%20Congress%20of%20supporting%20a%20%26quot%3Bgenocidal%26quot%3B%20call%20against%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUdhayanidhi%20Stalin%20responded%20to%20the%20criticism%20on%20social%20media%2C%20denying%20that%20he%20called%20for%20the%20genocide%20of%20those%20following%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20argued%20that%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%3C%2Fem%3E%20perpetuates%20social%20divisions%20based%20on%20caste%20and%20religion%20and%20is%20fundamentally%20opposed%20to%20equality%20and%20social%20justice.%20The%20Tamil%20Nadu%20minister%20said%20he%20was%20ready%20to%20present%20the%20extensive%20writings%20of%20social%20activist%20Periyar%20and%20Dr%20BR%20Ambedkar%2C%20who%20conducted%20in-depth%20research%20on%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20ready%20to%20present%20the%20extensive%20writings%20of%20Periyar%20and%20Ambedkar%2C%20who%20conducted%20in-depth%20research%20on%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20its%20negative%20impact%20on%20society%20in%20any%20forum.%20Let%20me%20reiterate%20the%20crucial%20aspect%20of%20my%20speech%3A%20I%20believe%2C%20like%20the%20spread%20of%20diseases%20like%20COVID-19%2C%20Dengue%2C%20and%20Malaria%20by%20mosquitoes%2C%20that%20%3Cem%3ESanatana%20Dharma%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20responsible%20for%20many%20social%20evils%2C%26quot%3B%20Udhayanidhi%20Stalin%20wrote%20in%20a%20social%20media%20post%20last%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20prepared%20to%20confront%20any%20challenges%20that%20come%20my%20way%2C%20whether%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law%20or%20the%20people's%20court.%20Stop%20spreading%20fake%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709545800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fbnti32n4_udhayanidhi-stalin_625x300_02_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fyoure-not-a-layman-supreme-court-raps-mk-stalins-son-on-sanatana-row-5173043%22%2C%22