munity%20from%20prosecution%20if%20he%2Fshe%20is%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20for%20a%20vote%20or%20a%20speech%20in%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20by%20the%20seven-judge%20Constitution%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20explained%20in%20the%20judgment%20why%20the%20legal%20shield%20provided%20to%20lawmakers%20will%20not%20protect%20them%20in%20cases%20of%20bribery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20Immunity%20for%20Lawmakers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticles%20105%20and%20194%20of%20the%20Constitution%20protect%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20from%20prosecution%20to%20enable%20them%20to%20work%20without%20the%20fear%20of%20legal%20action%20against%20them.%20These%20provisions%20provide%20them%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20protect%20them%20from%20being%20prosecuted%20for%20their%20remarks%20in%20the%20House%20or%20any%20vote%20in%20Parliament%20or%20a%20House%20committee%20he%2Fshe%20may%20be%20part%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20an%20MP%20or%20an%20MLA%20cannot%20face%20a%20defamation%20case%20for%20any%20remark%20made%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House.%20If%20a%20lawmaker%20makes%20an%20objectionable%20remark%2C%20the%20Speaker%20-%20and%20not%20courts%20-%20will%20take%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%201998%20Judgment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday's%20verdict%20set%20aside%20the%201998%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%20case.%20In%20July%201993%2C%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20against%20the%20minority%20government%20led%20by%20the%20former%20Prime%20Minister.%20His%20government%20had%20survived%20with%20a%20slim%20margin%20-%20265%20votes%20in%20favour%20and%20251%20against.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20allegations%20surfaced%20that%20legislators%20of%20Jharkhand%20Mukti%20Morcha%20had%20taken%20bribes%20to%20vote%20in%20support%20of%20the%20government.%20In%20the%201998%20ruling%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20with%20a%203%3A2%20majority%20that%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20were%20immune%20from%20prosecution%20in%20bribery%20cases%20for%20their%20vote%20provided%20they%20kept%20their%20side%20of%20the%20bargain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Court%20Said%20Today%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20held%20that%20taking%20a%20bribe%20is%20an%20independent%20crime%20and%20it%20has%20no%20link%20with%20what%20a%20lawmaker%20says%20or%20does%20inside%20the%20Parliament%20or%20legislative%20assembly.%20Hence%2C%20the%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20enjoyed%20by%20lawmakers%20will%20not%20shield%20them.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20protection%20granted%20under%20Articles%20105%20and%20194%20cannot%20protect%20lawmakers%20in%20bribery%20cases%20because%20they%20have%20no%20link%20with%20their%20duties%20as%20members%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20warned%20that%20such%20protection%20would%20create%20a%20section%20that%20can%20enjoy%20unregulated%20exemption%20from%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20corruption%20and%20bribery%20by%20legislators%20can%20potentially%20destroy%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20Indian%20Parliamentary%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20105%2C%20it%20said%2C%20is%20aimed%20at%20maintaining%20a%20conducive%20environment%20for%20discussions.%20When%20a%20member%20takes%20a%20bribe%20for%20a%20speech%2C%20this%20environment%20is%20disrupted%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EComments%20On%20the%201998%20Verdict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelivering%20the%20unanimous%20verdict%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20disagree%20with%20the%20judgment%20in%20PV%20Narasimha%20(case).%20The%20judgment%20in%20that%20case%20which%20granted%20immunity%20to%20legislators%20for%20taking%20bribes%20to%20cast%20votes%20has%20wide%20ramifications%20and%20is%20overruled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20that%20the%201998%20judgment%20results%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bparadoxical%20situation%26quot%3B%20where%20a%20legislator%20who%20accepts%20a%20bribe%20and%20votes%20accordingly%20is%20protected%2C%20and%20a%20legislator%20who%2C%20despite%20taking%20a%20bribe%2C%20votes%20independently%20is%20prosecuted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20This%20Verdict%20Means%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20several%20decades%2C%20cash-for-votes%20trading%20has%20been%20a%20massive%20challenge%20in%20preserving%20the%20sanctity%20of%20electoral%20mandates.%20Prior%20to%20today's%20judgment%2C%20no%20MP%20or%20MLA%20could%20be%20prosecuted%20if%20they%20took%20a%20bribe%20and%20cast%20their%20vote%20accordingly.%20But%20now%20they%20have%20lost%20this%20immunity.%20The%20court%20held%20that%20the%20crime%20was%20complete%20the%20moment%20a%20lawmaker%20accepted%20the%20bribe%2C%20and%20the%20immunity%20he%2Fshe%20enjoys%20inside%20the%20House%20won't%20provide%20protection%20in%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709543700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fc1l320oo_supreme-court-ani_625x300_23_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-explained-how-supreme-court-stripped-mps-mlas-of-immunity-in-bribery-cases-5173098%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20landmark%20verdict%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20ruled%20that%20an%20MP%20or%20MLA%20cannot%20claim%20immunity%20from%20prosecution%20if%20he%2Fshe%20is%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20bribe%20for%20a%20vote%20or%20a%20speech%20in%20the%20House.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-explained-how-supreme-court-stripped-mps-mlas-of-immunity-in-bribery-cases-5173098%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nita%20Ambani%20is%20the%20real%20