ly%20struggle%20of%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20population%20living%20in%20urban%20poverty.%20In%20Delhi%2C%20extreme%20temperatures%2C%20often%20attributed%20to%20climate%20change%2C%20have%20become%20increasingly%20common.%20The%20months%20from%20April%20to%20July%20bring%20intense%20heat.%20In%202022%2C%20India%20recorded%20203%20heatwave%20days%2C%20the%20highest%20in%20recent%20history%2C%20with%20Delhi%20accounting%20for%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fddma.delhi.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fddma%2Fgeneric_multiple_files%2Fnidm-heat_wave_action_plan_05.07.2023_1.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E17%20of%20those%20heatwave%20days%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20March%202022%20marked%20the%20hottest%20month%20ever%20recorded%20in%20India%20by%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20(IMD)%2C%20while%20Delhi%20experienced%20its%20second-hottest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fddma.delhi.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fddma%2Fgeneric_multiple_files%2Fnidm-heat_wave_action_plan_05.07.2023_1.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EApril%20in%2072%20years%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20inability%20of%20the%20economically%20weak%20to%20access%20adequate%20housing%20intensifies%20the%20harsh%20impacts%20of%20extreme%20climatic%20conditions%20and%20hinders%20the%20ability%20of%20communities%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fheat-waves-hit-the-poor-hardest-calculating-the-rising-impact-on-those-least-able-to-adapt-to-the-warming-climate-175224%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eadapt%20to%20escalating%20temperatures%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2Freport%2Far6%2Fwg1%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20United%20Nations%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC)%20identified%20India%20as%20one%20of%20the%20nations%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20consequences%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20Projections%20indicate%20that%20the%20country%20will%20witness%20more%20prolonged%20and%20frequent%20heat%20waves%20of%20heightened%20intensity%20in%20the%20future%2C%20increasing%20the%20risks%20for%20those%20living%20in%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20independent%20experts%20and%20estimates%2C%20in%20Delhi%2C%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hlrn.org.in%2Fdocuments%2FPress_Release_10_October_2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E200%2C000%E2%80%93250%2C000%20individuals%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20live%20in%20homelessness%2C%20including%20women%2C%20children%2C%20transgender%20persons%2C%20older%20individuals%2C%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20and%20other%20vulnerable%20groups.%20The%20Delhi%20Urban%20Shelter%20Improvement%20Board%20(DUSIB)%2C%20the%20principal%20agency%20addressing%20homelessness%20in%20Delhi%2C%20operates%20a%20network%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.delhishelterboard.in%2Foccupancy-report%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E195%20shelters%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%2082%20permanent%20structures%20(RCC%20buildings)%20in%20existing%20government%20buildings%2C%20103%20porta%20cabins%20made%20from%20tin%20sheets%2C%20and%2010%20shelters%20constructed%20under%20a%20%E2%80%98special%20drive%E2%80%99.%20Despite%20these%20efforts%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.delhishelterboard.in%2Foccupancy-report%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoverall%20capacity%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20these%20195%20shelters%20is%20around%2016%2C675%20beds%2C%20about%2092%25%20below%20the%20estimated%20population%20of%20homeless%20persons%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHomeless%20persons%20also%20find%20themselves%20exempt%20from%20national%20and%20state%20policies%20on%20housing%20%E2%80%93%20for%20example%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Awas%20Yojana%20(PMAY)%20%E2%80%93%20as%20they%20are%20unable%20to%20fulfil%20the%20eligibility%20requirements%20laid%20down%20in%20the%20schemes.%20The%20lack%20of%20identity%20documents%20and%20a%20permanent%20address%2C%20coupled%20with%20homelessness%20and%20absence%20of%20assets%20for%20securing%20a%20loan%2C%20systematically%20exclude%20individuals%20from%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFurthermore%2C%20there%20is%20no%20specific%20provision%20within%20the%20scheme%20for%20addressing%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20homeless.%20With%20no%20intermediary%20housing%20options%20or%20assistance%2C%20such%20as%20rental%20housing%20vouchers%20or%20hostels%2C%20a%20significant%20population%20is%20left%20with%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20live%20on%20the%20streets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EDespite%20the%20absence%20of%20official%20statistics%20on%20deaths%20of%20homeless%20persons%2C%20experts%20estimate%20that%20roughly%2060%25%20of%20%E2%80%98unidentified%20dead%20bodies%E2%80%99%20discovered%20by%20law%20enforcement%20and%20other%20agencies%20are%20those%20of%20homeless%20individuals.%20In%20Delhi%2C%20a%20significant%20majority%20of%20these%20deaths%20(4%2C424%20deaths)%20occurred%20during%20the%20summer%20months%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04102829%2Fimage-1896.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04102829%2Fimage-1896.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04102829%2Fimage-1896-300x180.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04102829%2Fimage-1896-1024x614.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699995%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22719%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Housing%20and%20Land%20Rights%20Network%20analysis%20based%20on%20Zonal%20Integrated%20Police%20Network%20data%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBetween%20May%20and%20June%202023%2C%20Housing%20and%20Land%20Rights%20Network%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hlrn.org.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHLRN%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20a%20non-profit%20organisation%20working%20in%20this%20sector%20for%2025%20years%2C%20undertook%20a%20rapid-assessment%20study%20to%20document%20the%20impact%20of%20rising%20temperatures%20on%20persons%20in%20Delhi%20without%20a%20home%2C%20assess%20their%20awareness%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20understand%20their%20adaptability%20to%20extreme%20weather%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20all%2C%20102%20homeless%20persons%20in%20Delhi%20participated%20in%20the%20study%2C%20representing%20diverse%20demographics%20including%20women%2C%20families%2C%20older%20individuals%2C%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20and%20other%20vulnerable%20groups.%20Around%2040%25%20of%20the%20respondents%20identified%20as%20women%20and%2060%25%20of%20them%20as%20men%2C%20spanning%20an%20age%20range%20of%2016%20to%2070%20years.%20The%20people%20surveyed%20experienced%20various%20forms%20of%20homelessness%3A%205.9%25%20in%20permanent%20shelters%2C%2017.6%25%20in%20porta%20cabins%2C%208.8%25%20in%20tarpaulin%20shanties%2C%20and%2067.7%25%20on%20the%20streets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20that%20heat%20waves%20do%20not%20impact%20everyone%20equally%20in%20a%20city%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiihs.co.in%2Fiihs-people%2Fteam%2Fchandni-singh%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChandni%2520is%2520a%2520Lead%2520Author%2CReport%2520on%25201.5%25C2%25B0C.%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EChandni%20Singh%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20senior%20researcher%20at%20Indian%20Institute%20for%20Human%20settlements%20and%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC)%20lead%20author.%20%E2%80%9CExtreme%20heat%20often%20follows%20and%20exposes%20existing%20faultlines%20of%20poverty%2C%20precarious%20livelihoods%2C%20and%20gender-%20and%20age-related%20vulnerabilities.%20Homeless%20people%20in%20particular%20are%20often%20invisibilised%20in%20heat%20vulnerability%20studies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPerception%20of%20climate%20change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMoolchand%2C%20aged%2050%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20a%20shelter%20near%20Jamuna%20Bazar%2C%20Hanuman%20Mandir%2C%20reflects%20on%20the%20changing%20times%2C%20%E2%80%9CTen%20years%20ago%2C%20we%20could%20endure%20the%20summer%20with%20the%20assistance%20of%20coolers%2C%20fans%2C%20and%20trees.%20But%20now%2C%20they%20no%20longer%20provide%20any%20relief.%E2%80%9D%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhlrn.org.in%2Fdocuments%2FClimate_Change_and_the_Urban_Poor.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHLRN%E2%80%99s%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2091.2%25%20of%20respondents%20noted%20a%20surge%20in%20heat%2C%20with%2080%25%20reporting%20increased%20challenges%20due%20to%20rising%20temperatures%20over%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20participants%20of%20the%20study%20highlighted%20several%20reasons%20for%20the%20increase%20in%20temperatures.%20Alluding%20to%20the%20impact%20of%20urban%20development%2C%20Mintu%2C%20a%20waste%20picker%20in%20Nizamuddin%20and%20Khan%20Market%20who%20lives%20in%20a%20park%20in%20Nizamuddin%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CDue%20to%20the%20large%20buildings%20and%20bus%20traffic%2C%20the%20influence%20of%20heat%20is%20increasing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETwo%20in%20five%20of%20the%20homeless%20persons%20surveyed%20highlighted%20the%20surge%20in%20vehicular%20activity%20as%20a%20key%20factor%20contributing%20to%20the%20escalating%20heat.%20This%20aligns%20with%20findings%20from%20the%20IPCC%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Far5-syr.ipcc.ch%2Ftopic_observedchanges.php%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efifth%20assessment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20underscores%20the%20impact%20of%20anthropogenic%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20by%20vehicles%20(14.3%25)%20on%20rising%20temperatures.%20Despite%20lacking%20familiarity%20with%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98climate%20change%2C%E2%80%99%20homeless%20persons%E2%80%99%20interpretations%20and%20observations%20regarding%20the%20causes%20of%20extreme%20heat%20closely%20align%20with%20global%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFactors%20such%20as%20heightened%20air%20pollution%2C%20rapid%20industrialisation%2C%20urbanisation%2C%20deforestation%2C%20and%20conspicuous%20consumption%20among%20the%20affluent%20are%20also%20identified%20by%20the%20populace%20as%20contributors%20to%20rising%20temperatures.%20Sunil%2C%20a%2042-year-old%20resident%20of%20a%20portable%20cabin%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20heat%20intensifies%20daily%20due%20to%20the%20construction%20of%20towering%20buildings.%20It%20stays%20really%20hot%20throughout%20the%20day%2C%20only%20cooling%20down%20after%202%20am.%20The%20problem%20is%20made%20worse%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20enough%20open%20land%20in%20Delhi%20to%20soak%20up%20rainwater.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EImpact%20of%20extreme%20heat%20on%20homeless%20people%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20effects%20of%20extreme%20heat%20are%20evident%20on%20the%20human%20body%2C%20the%20adverse%20impacts%20on%20homeless%20individuals%20are%20even%20more%20pronounced%2C%20as%20revealed%20by%20the%20investigation%20conducted%20by%20HLRN.%20Nearly%20everyone%20(99%25%20of%20individuals)%20living%20on%20the%20streets%20reported%20experiencing%20sleeplessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20effects%20of%20heat%20on%20the%20homeless%20population%20include%20heatstroke%2C%20weakness%2C%20an%20increase%20in%20vector-borne%20diseases%2C%20eye-related%20problems%2C%20diarrhoea%2C%20skin%20issues%20such%20as%20rashes%20and%20irritation%2C%20restlessness%2C%20difficulty%20in%20breathing%2C%20nausea%2C%20dizziness%2C%20vomiting%2C%20dehydration%2C%20elevated%20blood%20pressure%2C%20headaches%2C%20fever%2C%20coughing%2C%20cholera%2C%20frequent%20nosebleeds%2C%20loss%20of%20appetite%2C%20stomachache%2C%20and%20infections.%20Elevated%20temperatures%20and%20increased%20number%20of%20vectors%20%E2%80%93%20which%20can%20transmit%20infectious%20pathogens%20%E2%80%93%20compound%20the%20challenge%20of%20finding%20adequate%20outdoor%20sleeping%20arrangements%2C%20concurrently%20heightening%20health%20risks%20from%20food%20spoilage%20and%20contamination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFurther%2C%2045.1%25%20of%20individuals%20reported%20a%20deterioration%20in%20their%20existing%20health%20conditions%20due%20to%20the%20adverse%20impacts%20of%20extreme%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20inadequacy%20of%20basic%20infrastructure%20and%20cooling%20mechanisms%20exacerbates%20the%20impact%20of%20heat%20on%20homeless%20persons.%20Nazma%2C%2028%2C%20residing%20in%20Daryaganj%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20tarpaulin%20sheet%20becomes%20hot%20and%20tears%20by%20evening%2C%20and%20even%20simple%20tasks%20like%20making%20%3Ci%3Echapatis%3C%2Fi%3E%20(flatbread)%20becomes%20challenging%20due%20to%20the%20intense%20heat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EEven%20shelter%20homes%20prove%20ineffective%20in%20the%20summer.%20As%20Moolchand%20from%20the%20Jamuna%20Bazar%20shelter%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFans%20in%20the%20shelter%20blow%20warm%20air%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20sleep%20throughout%20the%20night%20due%20to%20the%20warmth%20inside.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPorta%20cabins%2C%20which%20are%20intended%20to%20serve%20as%20shelters%20for%20homeless%20persons%20but%20are%20constructed%20of%20thick%20tin%20sheets%2C%20become%20heat%20traps%20in%20summer%20and%20are%20rendered%20useless.%20A%2050-year-old%20man%20living%20in%20a%20porta%20cabin%20in%20Mayur%20Vihar%2C%20Delhi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20day%20progresses%2C%20the%20porta%20cabin%20gets%20very%20hot%20and%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20stay%20inside.%20We%20have%20to%20sit%20in%20a%20nearby%20park%20under%20the%20tree%20during%20the%20day.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fclimatechange%2Fadelle-thomas-loss-and-damage%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELoss%20and%20damage%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20often%20associated%20with%20the%20unavoidable%20or%20unprevented%20adverse%20effects%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20is%20typically%20discussed%20in%20the%20broader%20context%20of%20economic%20losses.%20However%2C%20for%20homeless%20individuals%2C%20the%20loss%20of%20possessions%20may%20not%20entail%20immovable%20assets%20like%20a%20house%2C%20but%20rather%20damage%20to%20essential%20daily%20items%2C%20such%20as%20perishable%20goods%20like%20food%20and%20vegetables.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFor%20instance%2C%2056%25%20reported%20food%20spoilage%20as%20a%20problem.%20Baby%20Kumar%2C%2023%2C%20residing%20in%20the%20Sarai%20Kale%20Khan%20shelter%20home%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CVegetables%20go%20bad%2C%20tomatoes%20and%20onions%20rot%20due%20to%20the%20heat%2C%20and%20the%20food%20we%20prepare%20in%20the%20morning%20turns%20bad%20by%20evening.%20Even%20the%20water%20becomes%20hot.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELivelihood%20and%20labour%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20International%20Labour%20Organization%20(ILO)%20in%202019%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fwcmsp5%2Fgroups%2Fpublic%2F---dgreports%2F---dcomm%2F---publ%2Fdocuments%2Fpublication%2Fwcms_711919.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eprojected%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20if%20current%20global%20warming%20trends%20persist%2C%20the%20total%20share%20of%20working%20hours%20lost%20will%20escalate%20to%202.2%25%20by%202030.%20This%20translates%20to%20the%20loss%20of%2080%20million%20full-time%20jobs%20or%20%242.4%20trillion%20in%20lost%20incomes.%20The%20findings%20of%20HLRN%E2%80%99s%20study%20align%20with%20these%20projections%2C%20as%20many%20homeless%20individuals%20are%20employed%20in%20outdoor%20work%20in%20informal%20settings%2C%20such%20as%20daily-wage%20manual%20labour%2C%20rickshaw%20pulling%2C%20selling%20goods%20at%20traffic%20signals%2C%20waste%20picking%20and%20segregation%2C%20construction%20work%2C%20street%20vending%2C%20and%20begging%20for%20sustenance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EShrafat%2C%2056%2C%20residing%20on%20the%20street%20near%20Sunehri%20Masjid%20and%20working%20as%20a%20rickshaw%20puller%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%E2%80%99t%20work%20after%20one%20ride.%20It%E2%80%99s%20disheartening%20to%20seek%20another%20ride%2C%20and%20the%20rickshaw%E2%80%99s%20wheel%20gets%20weak%20and%20punctured%2C%20causing%20additional%20problems.%E2%80%9D%20He%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20cook%20rotis%20in%20the%20heat.%20Working%20becomes%20difficult%3B%20we%20start%20feeling%20nauseous.%20It%E2%80%99s%20challenging%20to%20work%20continuously.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20heat-induced%20loss%20of%20productivity%20further%20hampers%20the%20ability%20of%20the%20homeless%20to%20earn%20a%20decent%20living.%20On%20average%2C%20respondents%20earn%20less%20than%20%24100%20(Rs%208%2C000)%20per%20month%2C%20limiting%20their%20capacity%20to%20cope%20with%20the%20impact%20of%20extreme%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAfsana%2C%2023%2C%20a%20daily%20wage%20worker%20living%20on%20the%20streets%20in%20Nizammudin%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20fall%20sick%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20money%20for%20treatment%20or%20sometimes%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20complete%20the%20course%20of%20medicine.%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Directorate%20General%20of%20Health%20Services%20in%20Delhi%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20initiatives%20taken%20by%20the%20health%20department%20for%20the%20homeless%20population.%20We%20will%20update%20this%20story%20when%20we%20receive%20a%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EClimate%20adaptation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIndividuals%20experiencing%20homelessness%20lack%20access%20to%20essential%20resources%20such%20as%20potable%20water%2C%20nutritious%20food%2C%20and%20healthcare%20%E2%80%93%20crucial%20elements%20for%20safeguarding%20against%20the%20rigours%20of%20intense%20heat.%20Around%2035%25%20of%20the%20surveyed%20homeless%20people%20stated%20that%20they%20lack%20access%20to%20drinking%20water%2C%20electricity%2C%20food%2C%20toilets%2C%20and%20cooling%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHousing%20plays%20a%20central%20role%20in%20safeguarding%20individuals%20from%20the%20adverse%20impacts%20of%20heat%20and%20climate%20change.%20However%2C%20the%20unavailability%20of%20adequate%20housing%20restricts%20access%20to%20essential%20resources%20such%20as%20water%2C%20food%2C%20health%2C%20education%2C%20and%20even%20livelihood.%20The%20human%20right%20to%20adequate%20housing%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FDocuments%2FIssues%2FHousing%2FJustice%2FHousingLandRightsNetwork.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaffirmed%20by%20the%20judiciary%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20integral%20component%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%20The%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20adequate%20housing%2C%20thus%2C%20leaves%20an%20individual%20susceptible%20to%20various%20other%20human%20rights%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20adequacy%20of%20their%20places%20of%20stay%20in%20providing%20protection%20from%20extreme%20heat%20and%20weather%2C%20none%20of%20the%20surveyed%20individuals%20stated%20that%20their%20living%20arrangements%20were%20sufficient.%20Fewer%20than%204%25%20of%20the%20respondents%20mentioned%20that%20their%20places%20provided%20a%20little%20protection%20but%20not%20adequately.%20Chandan%2C%2045%2C%20from%20Yamuna%20Khadar%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20only%20have%20this%20hut%20that%20is%20providing%20us%20shelter%3B%20apart%20from%20that%2C%20we%20have%20no%20other%20means%20of%20protection%20or%20facilities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20access%20to%20drinking%20water%20is%20crucial%20to%20prevent%20heat%20strokes%2C%2095.1%25%20of%20people%20are%20unable%20to%20obtain%20the%20water%20necessary%20to%20stay%20cool%20during%20the%20summer.%20People%20we%20spoke%20to%20pointed%20out%20that%20earlier%2C%20water%20was%20available%20through%20public%20taps%2C%20but%20now%20it%20has%20to%20be%20bought.%20Similarly%2C%20bathing%20involves%20paying%20to%20use%20public%20toilets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20severity%20of%20the%20situation%20is%20more%20pronounced%20for%20those%20living%20on%20the%20streets%2C%20but%20conditions%20in%20shelters%20are%20not%20significantly%20better.%20Among%20respondents%20living%20in%20shelter%20homes%20or%20porta%20cabins%2C%2012%25%20reported%20unavailability%20of%20drinking%20water%2C%20and%2021%25%20mentioned%20a%20lack%20of%20electricity.%20Further%2C%2074.3%25%20of%20people%20on%20the%20streets%20and%20in%20shelters%20pointed%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20cooling%20devices%20like%20fans%20or%20coolers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFurther%2C%2085%25%20of%20the%20respondents%20living%20on%20the%20streets%20emphasised%20the%20absence%20of%20access%20to%20public%20toilet%20facilities%2C%20sometimes%20forcing%20them%20to%20defecate%20in%20the%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20addition%2C%2078%25%20of%20the%20respondents%20mentioned%20having%20no%20access%20to%20healthcare%20and%20medicines.%20Around%2074%25%20of%20the%20respondents%20also%20reported%20no%20access%20to%20parks%20and%20open%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecommendations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20Government%20of%20Delhi%20takes%20special%20steps%20to%20respond%20during%20the%20winter%20months%2C%20it%20does%20not%20have%20any%20significant%20plans%20for%20summer%2Fheat%20or%20monsoons%2C%20specifically%20for%20homeless%20persons.%20This%20results%20in%20homeless%20persons%20having%20to%20fend%20for%20themselves%20during%20these%20equally%20harsh%20seasons%20and%20deal%20with%20extreme%20temperatures%2C%20heat%20waves%2C%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20and%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20adequate%20and%20affordable%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20Delhi%20Disaster%20Management%20Authority%20launched%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fddma.delhi.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fddma%2Fgeneric_multiple_files%2Fnidm-heat_wave_action_plan_05.07.2023_1.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHeat%20Action%20Plan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20does%20not%20address%20or%20accommodate%20the%20specific%20needs%20of%20homeless%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20shelters%20may%20not%20be%20entirely%20sufficient%2C%20they%20still%20offer%20a%20sense%20of%20refuge%20and%20protection.%20For%20example%2C%20most%20of%20these%20shelters%20provide%20food%20and%20better%20access%20to%20services%20such%20as%20drinking%20water%20and%20fans%20compared%20to%20those%20living%20on%20the%20streets.%20Despite%20concerted%20efforts%20by%20the%20DUSIB%20to%20safeguard%20the%20homeless%20during%20winter%20by%20erecting%20temporary%20tents%2C%20a%20critical%20gap%20emerges%20as%20these%20erected%20tents%20are%20routinely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hlrn.org.in%2Fdocuments%2FHLRN_Summer_Plan_Homelessness_Delhi_April_2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edisassembled%20by%20the%20end%20of%20March%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20thereby%20exposing%20people%20to%20the%20elements%20and%20depriving%20them%20of%20essential%20services%20such%20as%20water%2C%20meals%2C%20and%20sanitary%20facilities%20through%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20lack%20of%20shelters%20is%20a%20pressing%20issue%2C%20In%20March%202023%2C%20the%20DUSIB%20had%20demolished%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1045610%2Fare-shelters-for-the-homeless-in-delhi-being-demolished-for-g20%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eeight%20shelter%20homes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20city%2C%20rendering%20many%20individuals%20homeless.%20Evictions%20and%20forced%20demolitions%20of%20slums%20and%20houses%20exacerbate%20the%20issue%20even%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hlrn.org.in%2Fdocuments%2FHLRN_Summer_Plan_Homelessness_Delhi_April_2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESummer%20Action%20Plan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20HLRN%20highlights%20the%20need%20for%20enhanced%20facilities%20and%20services%20in%20existing%20shelters.%20This%20includes%20ensuring%20a%20consistent%20supply%20of%20potable%20water%20for%20drinking%2C%20as%20well%20as%20clean%20water%20for%20bathing%2C%20washing%20clothes%2C%20and%20fulfilling%20other%20personal%20needs%20at%20all%20shelters.%20Moreover%2C%20the%20plan%20advocates%20for%20the%20installation%20of%20functional%20air%20coolers%20and%20fans%20in%20all%20shelters%2C%20encompassing%20both%20porta%20cabins%20and%20reinforced%20concrete%20cement%20buildings.%20Special%20attention%20is%20urged%20to%20improve%20ventilation%2C%20particularly%20in%20structures%20made%20with%20tin.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20implementation%20of%20regular%20pest-%20and%20vector-control%20measures%20is%20emphasised%20across%20all%20shelters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20these%20short-term%20measures%20can%20mitigate%20some%20of%20the%20harsh%20impacts%20of%20extreme%20weather%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20only%20a%20comprehensive%20national%20policy%20on%20homelessness%20with%20a%20long%20term%20plan%20to%20secure%20diverse%20forms%20of%20housing%20for%20the%20homeless%20can%20protect%20them%20from%20the%20actual%20dangers%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESoumya%20Dutta%2C%20co-convener%2C%20South%20Asian%20people%E2%80%99s%20Action%20on%20Climate%20Crisis%20(SAPACC)%2C%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20worst%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20%E2%80%93%20severe%20heat%20waves%2C%20increased%20urban%20flooding%2C%20more%20frequent%20urban%20fires%20%E2%80%93%20in%20urban%20environments%20are%20on%20the%20homeless%2C%20those%20doing%20physical%20work%20outdoors%20and%20those%20living%20in%20heavily%20congested%20shanties%20and%20slums.%20There%20is%20little%20recognition%20of%20the%20multiple%20vulnerabilities%20these%20people%20face%2C%20let%20alone%20learning%20from%20their%20lived%20experiences%20and%20incorporating%20these%20in%20the%20State%20Action%20Plans%20for%20Climate%20Change%20or%20city%20level%20heat%20action%20plans%20(HAPs)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20written%20to%20the%20DUSIB%20asking%20for%20additional%20details%20about%20existing%20measures%20and%20future%20plans.%20We%20will%20update%20this%20story%20when%20we%20receive%20a%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Fearthcheckindia%2Fhow-delhis-homeless-people-struggle-during-hot-summers-896771%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20IndiaSpend.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709530377000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F04105726%2Fimage-1897.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwait-for-early-morning-to-catch-some-sleep-ho